82
00:03:56,369 --> 00:03:58,805
Edward Lee!

83
00:03:58,871 --> 00:04:00,873
Eddie, welcome to <i>Chef & My Fridge</i>!

84
00:04:00,940 --> 00:04:02,141
It's great to have you.

85
00:04:07,981 --> 00:04:10,717
HE ALWAYS USES HIS IDENTITY

86
00:04:10,783 --> 00:04:14,087
TO MAKE CREATIVE AND
NOVEL DISHES EVERY SINGLE TIME

87
00:04:14,153 --> 00:04:16,723
THE SECOND PLACE
OF CULINARY CLASS WARS

88
00:04:16,789 --> 00:04:19,626
EDWARD LEE

89
00:04:19,692 --> 00:04:21,561
Welcome to <i>Chef & My Fridge</i>.

90
00:04:24,931 --> 00:04:26,432
He says this is a special day.

91
00:04:26,499 --> 00:04:28,434
And this man.

92
00:04:28,501 --> 00:04:30,570
-I wanted to meet him.
-A man with many fans.

93
00:04:30,637 --> 00:04:33,172
The winner of <i>MasterChef Korea</i>,

94
00:04:33,239 --> 00:04:35,508
the braising fairy of <i>Culinary Class Wars</i>,

95
00:04:35,575 --> 00:04:39,379
-"It's me," Choi Kang-rok!
-Welcome to the show!

96
00:04:40,647 --> 00:04:42,382
"It's me, perilla oil."

97
00:04:42,448 --> 00:04:44,951
THE TOP GUN OF BRAISED DISHES

98
00:04:45,018 --> 00:04:48,588
I have to add oyster as gar…
Yes, as garnish.

99
00:04:48,655 --> 00:04:49,656
<i>I won't be an NPC.</i>

100
00:04:49,722 --> 00:04:51,591
ALWAYS OUT MAKING MEMES

101
00:04:51,658 --> 00:04:54,127
CHEF CHOI KANG-ROK

102
00:04:54,861 --> 00:04:56,696
He looks a bit nervous.

103
00:04:56,763 --> 00:04:58,731
-He does have that shyness.
-Yes.

104
00:04:58,798 --> 00:05:01,634
-I think he's about to cry.
-Tell me about it.

105
00:05:01,701 --> 00:05:04,704
-Stay calm.
-Stay calm.

106
00:05:04,771 --> 00:05:06,806
It's nice to meet you, Chef Choi.

107
00:05:06,873 --> 00:05:09,542
She captured the taste
of a three-star Michelin chef,

108
00:05:09,609 --> 00:05:12,211
a legendary cook, Master of School Meals,

109
00:05:12,278 --> 00:05:15,048
Lee Mi-yeong!

110
00:05:15,114 --> 00:05:15,982
MASTER OF SCHOOL MEALS,
LEE MI-YEONG

111
00:05:16,049 --> 00:05:18,851
A FORMER SCHOOL CHEF
WHO WAS IN CHARGE

112
00:05:19,585 --> 00:05:20,420
OF COOKING FOR KIDS

113
00:05:20,486 --> 00:05:22,155
What's for lunch today?

114
00:05:23,089 --> 00:05:24,223
<i>My appetite is like a kid's.</i>

115
00:05:24,290 --> 00:05:25,992
<i>but it was delicious.</i>

116
00:05:26,059 --> 00:05:28,928
I remembered memories from my childhood.

117
00:05:28,995 --> 00:05:31,364
CHEF LEE MI-YEONG

118
00:05:31,431 --> 00:05:35,568
She's now here to become
the goddess of <i>Chef & My Fridge</i>,

119
00:05:35,635 --> 00:05:37,470
the goddess of Chinese cuisine,

120
00:05:37,537 --> 00:05:40,173
-Park Eun-yeong!
-Welcome to the show!

121
00:05:40,239 --> 00:05:43,042
THE RISING CHINESE CHEF

122
00:05:43,109 --> 00:05:45,311
She must be your student.

123
00:05:45,378 --> 00:05:47,747
She can do everything I can,

124
00:05:47,814 --> 00:05:50,650
so the Goddess of Chinese Cuisine
will make it.

125
00:05:50,717 --> 00:05:51,551
<i>You survived.</i>

126
00:05:51,617 --> 00:05:53,920
CHEF PARK EUN-YEONG

127
00:05:53,986 --> 00:05:55,988
Four chefs, please have a seat.

128
00:05:56,055 --> 00:05:58,624
-I should pull the chairs out.
-Yes, pull them out.

129
00:05:58,691 --> 00:06:01,627
-My gosh, they're here.
-It's nice to meet you.

130
00:06:01,694 --> 00:06:02,829
A HISTORICAL FIRST ENCOUNTER

131
00:06:02,895 --> 00:06:04,630
OF CHEF & MY FRIDGE
AND CULINARY CLASS WARS

132
00:06:04,697 --> 00:06:07,200
You should all meet each other.

133
00:06:07,266 --> 00:06:08,501
Attention.

134
00:06:08,568 --> 00:06:09,435
And bow.

135
00:06:09,502 --> 00:06:11,637
IT'S NICE TO MEET YOU

136
00:06:11,704 --> 00:06:13,005
Yes, right.

137
00:06:13,072 --> 00:06:15,541
As soon as the lineup was released,

138
00:06:15,608 --> 00:06:19,112
these prestigious chefs captured
the eyes of many

139
00:06:19,178 --> 00:06:21,614
-and became the biggest issue.
-People are going crazy.

140
00:06:21,681 --> 00:06:24,584
Edward Lee, you're now here

141
00:06:24,650 --> 00:06:26,285
as a cast of <i>Chef & My Fridge</i>.

142
00:06:26,352 --> 00:06:28,388
I want to know how you feel.

143
00:06:28,454 --> 00:06:30,857
I came

144
00:06:30,923 --> 00:06:34,360
to Korea in a 15-hour flight.

145
00:06:34,427 --> 00:06:37,196
-I see.
-Just because of this.

146
00:06:37,263 --> 00:06:39,832
-It was that important.
-I see.

147
00:06:39,899 --> 00:06:41,667
-It's great to be here.
-Yes.

148
00:06:41,734 --> 00:06:45,772
How have you been doing
after <i>Culinary Class Wars</i>?

149
00:06:45,838 --> 00:06:48,741
I recently opened a new restaurant.

150
00:06:48,808 --> 00:06:50,810
-You opened a new restaurant?
-Another one?

151
00:06:50,877 --> 00:06:52,845
-Three weeks ago.
-Where is it?

152
00:06:52,912 --> 00:06:54,647
-Washington DC.
-Washington DC.

153
00:06:54,714 --> 00:06:59,285
-I heard you lived in Kentucky.
-I do.

154
00:06:59,352 --> 00:07:02,522
Chef Lee does resemble a certain Kentucky.

155
00:07:02,588 --> 00:07:04,490
-The colonel.
-What certain Kentucky?

156
00:07:04,557 --> 00:07:07,059
-The chicken face.
-The chicken face.

157
00:07:07,126 --> 00:07:08,661
-Yes.
-You love chicken.

158
00:07:08,728 --> 00:07:13,299
There is a lot of interest in
Chef Edward Lee after the show's release.

159
00:07:13,366 --> 00:07:16,202
Does the popularity feel real to you?

160
00:07:16,269 --> 00:07:20,540
-It's wonderful to have many fans.
-Yes, you have lots of fans.

161
00:07:20,606 --> 00:07:22,975
But I was a little surprised.

162
00:07:23,042 --> 00:07:23,910
-You were?
-Yes.

163
00:07:23,976 --> 00:07:27,213
When I came to Korea,

164
00:07:27,280 --> 00:07:30,983
everyone wanted a picture with me
and my autograph.

165
00:07:31,050 --> 00:07:33,319
I heard Chef Yeon-bok wanted to meet him.

166
00:07:33,386 --> 00:07:35,254
-Yes.
-He was a huge fan.

167
00:07:35,321 --> 00:07:37,190
Yes, I thought he was really cool

168
00:07:37,256 --> 00:07:40,827
on <i>Culinary Class Wars</i>,
during the tofu hell round.

169
00:07:40,893 --> 00:07:42,695
You should say hi to him in English.

170
00:07:46,632 --> 00:07:48,801
Many Koreans
began to salt their food like this

171
00:07:48,868 --> 00:07:51,704
-all because of Chef Hyun-suk.
-You're right.

172
00:07:51,771 --> 00:07:54,540
Well, I'm done with salting food like that

173
00:07:54,607 --> 00:07:56,075
and being funny.

174
00:07:56,142 --> 00:07:58,711
-My sole focus is cooking.
-Right. Sure.

175
00:07:58,778 --> 00:08:01,113
Then you shouldn't be here.

176
00:08:01,180 --> 00:08:02,248
You have to be funny here.

177
00:08:02,315 --> 00:08:04,617
-That's what people expect from you.
-No.

178
00:08:04,684 --> 00:08:07,453
I need to show them
that cooking can be fun in itself.

179
00:08:07,520 --> 00:08:09,956
Why do you try to turn it into a joke?

180
00:08:10,022 --> 00:08:11,891
Did you just admit it had all been a joke?

181
00:08:11,958 --> 00:08:13,793
That wasn't what I meant.

182
00:08:13,860 --> 00:08:16,996
You're still doing… Enough is enough.

183
00:08:17,063 --> 00:08:18,431
The cat and dog are back.

184
00:08:18,498 --> 00:08:19,799
Why am I sitting next to him?

185
00:08:19,866 --> 00:08:22,101
Why did you put them next to each other?

186
00:08:22,168 --> 00:08:23,803
-I feel ill at ease.
-Sure.

187
00:08:28,040 --> 00:08:31,110
Are you an American? Who are you?

188
00:08:31,177 --> 00:08:34,380
I heard you wanted to continue working
with <i>Culinary Class Wars</i>.

189
00:08:34,447 --> 00:08:35,314
-He said that?
-Yes.

190
00:08:35,381 --> 00:08:37,850
-He preferred it to this show.
-Yes, I heard it too.

191
00:08:37,917 --> 00:08:40,319
-He didn't care much for <i>Chef & My Fridge</i>.
-I see.

192
00:08:40,386 --> 00:08:42,588
No, I had been

193
00:08:42,655 --> 00:08:44,991
-on both <i>Chef & My Fridge</i>
-Yes.

194
00:08:45,057 --> 00:08:47,360
and <i>Culinary Class Wars</i>.

195
00:08:47,426 --> 00:08:50,296
So, that makes me

196
00:08:50,363 --> 00:08:51,864
a man of mixed culture.

197
00:08:51,931 --> 00:08:53,065
THAT'S MY THING

198
00:08:53,132 --> 00:08:54,400
-A man of mixed culture.
-Mixed culture.

199
00:08:54,467 --> 00:08:56,335
CULINARY CLASS & MY FRIDGE(?)

200
00:08:56,402 --> 00:08:58,404
You said you wouldn't joke around,
but you did.

201
00:08:58,471 --> 00:09:01,807
I wasn't joking around.
I copied him because it was cool.

202
00:09:01,874 --> 00:09:03,576
THE ORIGINATOR
IS JUST HAVING FUN

203
00:09:03,643 --> 00:09:06,812
And this man. He's always in a hat.

204
00:09:06,879 --> 00:09:09,782
Chef Choi Kang-rok.

205
00:09:09,849 --> 00:09:13,219
I received a tip from the production crew
that you are quite shy.

206
00:09:13,286 --> 00:09:15,254
-That you were reserved.
-Right.

207
00:09:15,321 --> 00:09:18,524
So I was told
not to be coercive during my interviews,

208
00:09:18,591 --> 00:09:20,293
for I may fail altogether.

209
00:09:20,359 --> 00:09:22,728
I feel quite cautious
as I talk to Chef Kang-rok.

210
00:09:22,795 --> 00:09:26,699
Are you in good enough condition
to have a chat right now?

211
00:09:27,400 --> 00:09:28,968
-Can you put me off?
-Put you off?

212
00:09:29,035 --> 00:09:31,337
Should I come back to you after everyone?

213
00:09:31,404 --> 00:09:32,905
He's not quite ready.

214
00:09:32,972 --> 00:09:35,575
-I prepared something for Chef Kang-rok.
-What is it?

215
00:09:35,641 --> 00:09:38,778
If he wants to speak
while we're all talking,

216
00:09:38,844 --> 00:09:40,746
-he can lift the carrot.
-I see.

217
00:09:40,813 --> 00:09:43,382
-You'll see the carrot.
-There's a carrot.

218
00:09:43,449 --> 00:09:45,618
-He's shy.
-That was why he got that.

219
00:09:45,685 --> 00:09:48,821
So if you hold it up,
we'll stop and listen to you.

220
00:09:48,888 --> 00:09:51,724
-Anytime.
-Give us a sign. How will you do it?

221
00:09:51,791 --> 00:09:53,659
Can you raise the carrot?

222
00:09:54,427 --> 00:09:56,329
HE BARELY MANAGES TO LIFT IT UP…

223
00:09:57,029 --> 00:09:59,565
-He doesn't seem as shy now.
-He seems a bit awkward.

224
00:09:59,632 --> 00:10:02,101
So please make use of the carrot.

225
00:10:02,168 --> 00:10:05,571
And this next chef is
someone you can't meet easily.

226
00:10:05,638 --> 00:10:09,308
Please welcome the Master of School Meals,
Chef Lee Mi-yeong.

227
00:10:09,375 --> 00:10:10,876
It's great to be here.

228
00:10:10,943 --> 00:10:14,413
-She doesn't have a restaurant of her own,
-No.

229
00:10:14,480 --> 00:10:18,284
-and you recently retired from the school.
-Yes.

230
00:10:18,351 --> 00:10:22,555
I believe there is no way for people
to taste your food. Is that true?

231
00:10:22,622 --> 00:10:24,123
-It is true.
-Goodness.

232
00:10:24,190 --> 00:10:25,224
Did you hear that?

233
00:10:25,291 --> 00:10:27,126
It's only available on <i>Chef & My Fridge</i>.

234
00:10:27,193 --> 00:10:30,196
-The guests who bring their fridges.
-Yes.

235
00:10:30,262 --> 00:10:32,298
-Have you retired, then?
-Yes.

236
00:10:32,365 --> 00:10:34,100
-You've hit that age.
-Yes.

237
00:10:35,468 --> 00:10:37,436
-I'm in my sixties now.
-Sixties.

238
00:10:37,503 --> 00:10:39,605
-Sixties. Your age?
-Yes.

239
00:10:39,672 --> 00:10:42,308
-You're already in your sixties?
-You're in your sixties.

240
00:10:42,375 --> 00:10:44,677
-You don't look that age.
-You don't.

241
00:10:44,744 --> 00:10:47,313
-I thought you were in your forties.
-Thank you.

242
00:10:47,380 --> 00:10:48,914
The school must miss you.

243
00:10:48,981 --> 00:10:51,250
They did. And the children too.

244
00:10:51,317 --> 00:10:52,551
-The children.
-They would be.

245
00:10:52,618 --> 00:10:55,221
-Like, "I should've had another bite."
-Yes.

246
00:10:55,287 --> 00:10:58,491
The school I worked at
didn't have too many students.

247
00:10:58,557 --> 00:11:00,993
-We had 120 people, including the staff.
-About 120.

248
00:11:01,060 --> 00:11:03,095
-That's not too many?
-Not too many.

249
00:11:03,162 --> 00:11:04,497
So you had to cook for 120.

250
00:11:04,563 --> 00:11:07,833
There were two of us there
cooking over two hours and 30 minutes

251
00:11:07,900 --> 00:11:12,171
-to make about 120 servings. Yes.
-You made 120 servings?

252
00:11:12,238 --> 00:11:13,072
It can't be easy.

253
00:11:13,139 --> 00:11:16,776
-I heard Chef Eun-yeong moved to Hong Kong
-Yes?

254
00:11:16,842 --> 00:11:18,411
after <i>Culinary Class Wars</i>.

255
00:11:18,477 --> 00:11:20,112
Yes, I live there now.

256
00:11:20,179 --> 00:11:21,814
I also flew in yesterday.

257
00:11:22,448 --> 00:11:24,050
Everyone is all over the world.

258
00:11:24,116 --> 00:11:27,586
I also got intel that Chef Eun-yeong
grew up watching <i>Chef & My Fridge</i>.

259
00:11:27,653 --> 00:11:32,892
That's right.
I even sent a video to apply as a new chef

260
00:11:32,958 --> 00:11:34,860
when the recruitment was opened.

261
00:11:34,927 --> 00:11:38,664
-But I never heard back.
-Are you serious?

262
00:11:38,731 --> 00:11:39,799
Really?

263
00:11:39,865 --> 00:11:42,001
But now I'm sitting here.

264
00:11:42,068 --> 00:11:44,303
So on my way here today, I thought,

265
00:11:44,370 --> 00:11:47,273
"Gosh, Eun-yeong. You made it."

266
00:11:47,339 --> 00:11:48,874
HOW CUTE

267
00:11:48,941 --> 00:11:50,476
-Why didn't we call?
-That was how I felt.

268
00:11:50,543 --> 00:11:54,680
Chef Kang-rok, isn't it about time
you raised the carrot once?

269
00:11:54,747 --> 00:11:56,582
Yes, we're now done, Chef Kang-rok.

270
00:11:57,516 --> 00:11:59,051
-Can we do it?
-Sure.

271
00:11:59,652 --> 00:12:02,221
-You can relax. Should we look away?
-My gosh.

272
00:12:02,288 --> 00:12:04,323
He could feel pressed if we looked.

273
00:12:04,390 --> 00:12:07,059
-Do you feel uncomfortable when we look?
-Do you?

274
00:12:07,126 --> 00:12:10,629
-Yes, please try to look away.
-I guess attention is

275
00:12:10,696 --> 00:12:13,866
-too much for you.
-Why don't we take a soda break?

276
00:12:13,933 --> 00:12:15,401
-Yes, let's do that.
-Yes, because

277
00:12:15,468 --> 00:12:17,937
-he's a bit shy.
-Let's have some.

278
00:12:18,003 --> 00:12:20,239
-Let's drink quietly.
-We can do that.

279
00:12:20,306 --> 00:12:22,141
We won't look at you as we talk.

280
00:12:22,208 --> 00:12:26,946
The chefs who were on <i>Culinary Class Wars</i>
rose to great popularity these days,

281
00:12:27,012 --> 00:12:30,316
so they've all been working hard,
striking while the iron was hot.

282
00:12:30,382 --> 00:12:32,885
But rumors say only this man

283
00:12:32,952 --> 00:12:36,088
has left the iron hot
and has gone off the grid.

284
00:12:36,155 --> 00:12:37,957
-He threw it away.
-He did.

285
00:12:38,023 --> 00:12:39,358
Chef Choi Kang-rok.

286
00:12:39,425 --> 00:12:41,761
People said you went off the grid.
Is that true?

287
00:12:44,930 --> 00:12:47,433
I jyust… My words…

288
00:12:47,500 --> 00:12:49,001
THE FIRST WORDS: I JYUST

289
00:12:49,068 --> 00:12:50,336
So you can speak.

290
00:12:50,402 --> 00:12:52,037
-I'm sorry to ask,
-My words…

291
00:12:52,104 --> 00:12:54,340
but try not to sound imperative.

292
00:12:54,406 --> 00:12:56,876
-Take your time and be gentle.
-All right.

293
00:12:56,942 --> 00:12:57,843
Be more gentle.

294
00:12:57,910 --> 00:13:02,548
Chef Kang-rok, have you been
hiding somewhere?

295
00:13:02,615 --> 00:13:04,517
Or is this a false rumor?

296
00:13:04,583 --> 00:13:06,585
-Did he want a short break?
-Did he?

297
00:13:06,652 --> 00:13:08,921
I was just sitting around.

298
00:13:08,988 --> 00:13:11,357
-You were just there as always?
-Yes.

299
00:13:11,423 --> 00:13:13,993
I was keeping an eye on the situation.

300
00:13:14,059 --> 00:13:16,028
I thought, "What is this?"

301
00:13:17,730 --> 00:13:20,166
Yes, it was an unfamiliar situation,

302
00:13:20,232 --> 00:13:21,834
so I just sat still,

303
00:13:21,901 --> 00:13:24,370
but someone must've said that.

304
00:13:24,436 --> 00:13:26,605
-And there was no hot iron.
-Come on.

305
00:13:27,373 --> 00:13:29,975
-I was eliminated early on.
-Right.

306
00:13:30,042 --> 00:13:32,945
-But you left an impression.
-A strong impression.

307
00:13:33,012 --> 00:13:35,881
I was eliminated early on,
so I just sat around.

308
00:13:35,948 --> 00:13:40,686
Yet you still agreed
to appear on <i>Chef & My Fridge</i>.

309
00:13:40,753 --> 00:13:41,720
What's the reason?

310
00:13:41,787 --> 00:13:45,257
-I turned it down at first.
-You did?

311
00:13:45,324 --> 00:13:46,425
AT FIRST, HE SAID NO

312
00:13:47,026 --> 00:13:51,363
The thing is, Ho-young and I go way back.

313
00:13:51,430 --> 00:13:53,032
-Chef Ho-young?
-Yes.

314
00:13:53,098 --> 00:13:57,403
Chef Kang-rok was an underclassman
while I studied culinary arts in Japan.

315
00:13:57,469 --> 00:13:59,071
The school in Osaka?

316
00:13:59,138 --> 00:14:01,707
-One of the top three schools worldwide.
-Yes.

317
00:14:01,774 --> 00:14:03,442
So he was an underclassman?

318
00:14:03,509 --> 00:14:06,111
Kang-rok said he wanted to work

319
00:14:06,178 --> 00:14:07,947
at the sushi restaurant I worked at,

320
00:14:08,013 --> 00:14:10,149
so I gave my position to him
when I came back.

321
00:14:10,216 --> 00:14:13,085
You let him take the part-time job
you had at the restaurant?

322
00:14:13,152 --> 00:14:15,955
"You can take this job I used to work."

323
00:14:16,021 --> 00:14:17,756
We had that kind of friendship.

324
00:14:17,823 --> 00:14:19,124
I wasn't sure

325
00:14:19,191 --> 00:14:22,194
if I could secure a position
at the new <i>Chef & My Fridge</i>.

326
00:14:22,261 --> 00:14:26,165
-So I decided to use Choi Kang-rok.
-I'm glad!

327
00:14:26,232 --> 00:14:28,701
If Kang-rok got in,
I thought I could secure a position

328
00:14:28,767 --> 00:14:31,470
or make at least one appearance
in the series,

329
00:14:31,537 --> 00:14:33,272
so I did my best to persuade him.

330
00:14:33,339 --> 00:14:34,940
Dragging Kang-rok in to get you in.

331
00:14:35,007 --> 00:14:36,575
That was how I ended up here.

332
00:14:36,642 --> 00:14:38,010
I see.

333
00:14:38,077 --> 00:14:42,248
-This relationship was special to me,
-The relationship was special.

334
00:14:42,314 --> 00:14:44,183
but I didn't know what he was thinking.

335
00:14:44,250 --> 00:14:47,553
-I didn't know he used me to get in.
-You didn't know?

336
00:14:47,620 --> 00:14:48,988
-It was our relationship.
-Relationship.

337
00:14:49,054 --> 00:14:53,692
Anyway, I'm worried because Chef Kang-rok
is known for his braised dishes.

338
00:14:53,759 --> 00:14:55,661
-He's the master.
-He is.

339
00:14:55,728 --> 00:14:57,630
But braising food takes a while,

340
00:14:57,696 --> 00:15:01,267
so the entire population is worried
if he could finish braising everything

341
00:15:01,333 --> 00:15:02,501
under 15 minutes.

342
00:15:02,568 --> 00:15:04,870
-You may run out of time doing that.
-Yes.

343
00:15:04,937 --> 00:15:07,006
Can you do that in 15 minutes?

344
00:15:07,072 --> 00:15:10,743
I never thought of 15 minutes,
the unit of time we're discussing,

345
00:15:10,809 --> 00:15:16,115
as a viable unit of time
to cook a dish from start to finish.

346
00:15:16,982 --> 00:15:20,052
-It's just enough time to clean.
-Clean?

347
00:15:20,119 --> 00:15:22,187
-Fifteen minutes.
-Washing the dishes?

348
00:15:22,254 --> 00:15:24,623
Chef Kang-rok, were you highly concerned?

349
00:15:24,690 --> 00:15:27,326
Yes, I began to worry a lot.

350
00:15:27,393 --> 00:15:29,929
My family said

351
00:15:29,995 --> 00:15:31,497
I even talked in my sleep.

352
00:15:32,064 --> 00:15:33,165
HE WAS SO WORRIED…

353
00:15:33,232 --> 00:15:34,066
Chef Kang-rok.

354
00:15:34,133 --> 00:15:37,803
-"I'm finished."
-"I'm finished"?

355
00:15:37,870 --> 00:15:41,840
I must've done something in my dream.

356
00:15:41,907 --> 00:15:43,242
In your dream.

357
00:15:43,309 --> 00:15:45,844
But I still couldn't finish
even in the dream.

358
00:15:45,911 --> 00:15:48,013
-You'll finish it today, then.
-Yes.

359
00:15:48,080 --> 00:15:50,282
You must've been stressed out.

360
00:15:51,250 --> 00:15:55,754
<i>Chef & My Fridge</i> finally came back
after five years.

361
00:15:56,388 --> 00:15:57,222
Today,

362
00:15:57,289 --> 00:15:59,658
we will have a battle

363
00:15:59,725 --> 00:16:04,263
between the returning chefs
and the challenging chefs.

364
00:16:04,330 --> 00:16:05,164
A battle here?

365
00:16:05,230 --> 00:16:06,632
Is that all right?

366
00:16:06,699 --> 00:16:09,234
It sounds okay for now.

367
00:16:09,301 --> 00:16:12,338
Yes, because I can't fight

368
00:16:12,404 --> 00:16:14,940
against Kim Poong from episode one.

369
00:16:15,007 --> 00:16:18,344
-It's such a relief.
-Yes, you'll be fighting this side.

370
00:16:18,410 --> 00:16:19,979
-Fight me.
-It sounds positive.

371
00:16:20,045 --> 00:16:21,080
You find this positive.

372
00:16:21,146 --> 00:16:25,884
Chef Edward, is there any one of them
you want to fight against?

373
00:16:26,885 --> 00:16:29,455
-Of course.
-There is one?

374
00:16:29,521 --> 00:16:32,191
-It'll be weird if he picks Kim Poong.
-Exactly.

375
00:16:33,359 --> 00:16:34,994
-It'll be fun.
-Yes.

376
00:16:35,060 --> 00:16:36,295
-But…
-"But"?

377
00:16:37,863 --> 00:16:41,500
This guy had a tough time
throughout <i>Culinary Class Wars</i>.

378
00:16:41,567 --> 00:16:43,635
-Choi Hyun-suk.
-Choi Hyun-suk.

379
00:16:43,702 --> 00:16:46,472
We became good friends,

380
00:16:46,538 --> 00:16:50,876
-so it'd be nice to fight him.
-You chose Chef Hyun-suk.

381
00:16:51,710 --> 00:16:54,847
You picked one of the strongest chefs,
just as I expected.

382
00:16:54,913 --> 00:16:58,350
-It means he's that confident.
-Yes, that's right.

383
00:16:58,417 --> 00:17:00,386
Chef Kang-rok,
did you have someone on your mind?

384
00:17:01,186 --> 00:17:02,788
Honestly speaking,

385
00:17:02,855 --> 00:17:04,923
I want to avoid everyone if I can.

386
00:17:04,990 --> 00:17:07,559
-Right. I see.
-Wait, then what?

387
00:17:07,626 --> 00:17:10,162
If you want to avoid them,
are you going to fight us?

388
00:17:10,929 --> 00:17:12,464
KANG-ROK: AVOID THEM IF I CAN

389
00:17:12,531 --> 00:17:14,299
-You can't avoid them.
-We're laymen.

390
00:17:14,366 --> 00:17:16,635
So I asked to be in the audience
before I came.

391
00:17:16,702 --> 00:17:18,070
-I see.
-I see.

392
00:17:18,137 --> 00:17:20,205
-But they said no.
-The audience?

393
00:17:20,272 --> 00:17:22,741
What about you, Chef Eun-yeong,
the Goddess of Chinese Cuisine?

394
00:17:23,308 --> 00:17:26,812
I want to compete with Chef Yeon-bok.

395
00:17:26,879 --> 00:17:31,884
He's one of the two biggest Chinese chefs
along with my teacher, Lu Chinglai,

396
00:17:31,950 --> 00:17:34,386
so I have the ambition
to contend with him.

397
00:17:34,453 --> 00:17:36,488
By any chance, did Chef Lu Chinglai

398
00:17:36,555 --> 00:17:38,690
-tell you to fight him?
-Was it an order?

399
00:17:38,757 --> 00:17:40,125
Are you under his order?

400
00:17:40,192 --> 00:17:41,693
He didn't say anything,

401
00:17:41,760 --> 00:17:43,962
but he did say he'd keep an eye on me.

402
00:17:44,029 --> 00:17:47,666
-That was as good as an order.
-Yes, you're right.

403
00:17:47,733 --> 00:17:49,902
-The young Chinese chef.
-Yes.

404
00:17:49,968 --> 00:17:51,270
-The young Chinese chef.
-The young one.

405
00:17:51,336 --> 00:17:53,806
-Are you calling him the old chef?
-The old Chinese chef.

406
00:17:53,872 --> 00:17:56,708
-I am old.
-The young Chinese chef.

407
00:17:56,775 --> 00:17:58,610
I'm a grandpa now.

408
00:17:58,677 --> 00:18:02,247
The old Chinese chef is aching everywhere.

409
00:18:02,314 --> 00:18:05,784
And now, it's time to welcome
the fridge owners.

410
00:18:05,851 --> 00:18:07,286
-Gosh.
-Yes.

411
00:18:07,352 --> 00:18:09,755
I wonder who the guests are.

412
00:18:09,822 --> 00:18:14,426
Let us present the fridge owners.
Please come on out.

413
00:18:14,493 --> 00:18:16,628
THE FRIDGE OWNERS ARE HERE

414
00:18:16,695 --> 00:18:18,197
WHY IS THE STUDIO

415
00:18:18,263 --> 00:18:19,798
SUDDENLY PLAYING MUSIC?

416
00:18:20,499 --> 00:18:22,034
HEY

417
00:18:22,601 --> 00:18:24,269
SUDDENLY TENSE

418
00:18:27,606 --> 00:18:29,108
Chefs, scream out loud!

419
00:18:30,008 --> 00:18:32,211
HERE TO CELEBRATE, TROT SINGER
YOUNTAK AND CHIMCHAKMAN

420
00:18:32,277 --> 00:18:33,946
Chefs, scream out loud!

421
00:18:35,514 --> 00:18:38,584
<i>Real, real, real, real, the real deal</i>

422
00:18:38,650 --> 00:18:41,787
<i>It's totally the real deal</i>

423
00:18:41,854 --> 00:18:44,456
<i>The real deal is here</i>

424
00:18:44,523 --> 00:18:45,757
<i>Chef & My Fridge</i>!

425
00:18:45,824 --> 00:18:47,059
All right!

426
00:18:48,060 --> 00:18:51,296
<i>Real, real, real, real, the real deal</i>

427
00:18:51,363 --> 00:18:54,800
<i>It's totally the real deal</i>

428
00:18:54,867 --> 00:18:59,671
<i>You'll cook like the real deal</i>

429
00:19:00,405 --> 00:19:03,575
CELEBRATING THE SHOW'S COMEBACK
WITH THE REAL PERFORMANCE!

430
00:19:03,642 --> 00:19:04,643
Thank you.

431
00:19:04,710 --> 00:19:07,412
Welcome, Youngtak and Chimchakman.
Please take your seat.

432
00:19:07,479 --> 00:19:09,348
-Hello.
-Welcome.

433
00:19:09,414 --> 00:19:11,250
-Why did I have to stand there?
-Yes, hello.

434
00:19:11,950 --> 00:19:13,485
-Hello.
-Hello.

435
00:19:13,552 --> 00:19:15,854
-Hello.
-Hello.

436
00:19:15,921 --> 00:19:17,756
Today's fridge owners are

437
00:19:17,823 --> 00:19:21,527
here to celebrate the return
of <i>Chef & My Fridge</i> after five years,

438
00:19:21,593 --> 00:19:24,163
a trot man and Chimchakman!

439
00:19:24,229 --> 00:19:26,298
TROT MAN & CHIMCHAKMAN

440
00:19:28,066 --> 00:19:30,302
-Thank you for the performance.
-Thank you.

441
00:19:30,369 --> 00:19:33,071
-Look how fancy they're dressed.
-They are.

442
00:19:33,138 --> 00:19:34,406
It's like an awards ceremony.

443
00:19:34,473 --> 00:19:35,674
I can tell that…

444
00:19:35,741 --> 00:19:37,976
-He's dressed like Chef Ahn Sung-jae.
-Chef Ahn.

445
00:19:38,043 --> 00:19:40,245
DRESSED LIKE CHEF AHN
ON CULINARY CLASS WARS

446
00:19:40,312 --> 00:19:42,781
They came here with a theme.

447
00:19:42,848 --> 00:19:44,950
-If I may make a prediction,
-Yes?

448
00:19:45,017 --> 00:19:46,885
-I'll be at a disadvantage today.
-Why?

449
00:19:46,952 --> 00:19:49,555
As soon as I saw that suit,
I had a feeling

450
00:19:49,621 --> 00:19:51,456
he wouldn't like my cooking.

451
00:19:52,191 --> 00:19:55,527
<i>Why are you coming out from there?</i>

452
00:19:55,594 --> 00:19:58,430
Why are you coming out from there?

453
00:19:58,497 --> 00:20:00,065
SUDDENLY FEELS BAD

454
00:20:00,132 --> 00:20:01,400
Was that made official?

455
00:20:01,466 --> 00:20:03,669
No. Never mind.

456
00:20:03,735 --> 00:20:07,172
-He suddenly jumped in.
-I was trying to be funny. We're close.

457
00:20:07,239 --> 00:20:09,408
The two are the same age, born in 1983.

458
00:20:09,474 --> 00:20:12,411
Chef Edward, Chef Hyun-suk, and you are

459
00:20:12,477 --> 00:20:14,279
the same age, born in 1972, right?

460
00:20:14,346 --> 00:20:15,547
-He's right.
-Really?

461
00:20:15,614 --> 00:20:17,316
-The three of us.
-As far as I know, yes.

462
00:20:17,382 --> 00:20:19,851
-The Year of the Mouse.
-The Year of the Mouse, yes.

463
00:20:19,918 --> 00:20:21,119
You two are the same age?

464
00:20:21,186 --> 00:20:23,055
Were you really born in 1972?

465
00:20:23,121 --> 00:20:24,623
Yes.

466
00:20:24,690 --> 00:20:26,858
Why? Does it seem like I'm lying?

467
00:20:28,293 --> 00:20:29,661
Don't I look pretty young?

468
00:20:29,728 --> 00:20:32,030
THE THREE ARE CONSCIOUS
OF EACH OTHER

469
00:20:32,097 --> 00:20:34,900
I thought you were older than me.

470
00:20:34,967 --> 00:20:36,335
-The three of you are the same age.
-Yes.

471
00:20:36,401 --> 00:20:38,270
-You two should talk casually.
-You're friends.

472
00:20:38,337 --> 00:20:40,706
We should talk casually.

473
00:20:40,772 --> 00:20:44,009
-But he said he was four days older.
-I see.

474
00:20:44,076 --> 00:20:47,012
-Four days?
-He was born on July 2nd.

475
00:20:47,079 --> 00:20:48,847
-Really?
-He said we weren't the same.

476
00:20:48,914 --> 00:20:50,916
-Did he nitpick over that?
-He said he was older.

477
00:20:50,983 --> 00:20:52,751
He's very particular.

478
00:20:52,818 --> 00:20:53,852
MAN WHO'S 4 DAYS OLDER

479
00:20:53,919 --> 00:20:55,954
Then may I be
a little more casual with you?

480
00:20:56,021 --> 00:20:57,422
-Yes, sure.
-Okay.

481
00:20:57,489 --> 00:20:59,625
-Hey, Ed.
-Okay.

482
00:20:59,691 --> 00:21:01,226
-What? "Ed"?
-Nice to meet you, Ed.

483
00:21:01,293 --> 00:21:03,061
What now? "Ed"?

484
00:21:03,629 --> 00:21:04,730
Ed?

485
00:21:04,796 --> 00:21:06,732
Can you also call me Sung-ju?

486
00:21:06,798 --> 00:21:08,900
-That way… Sung-ju.
-Sung-ju.

487
00:21:08,967 --> 00:21:11,570
-Nice to meet you, Ed.
-Nice to meet you.

488
00:21:11,637 --> 00:21:12,904
Hyun-suk, doing okay?

489
00:21:14,473 --> 00:21:15,841
You don't look a day older.

490
00:21:17,376 --> 00:21:18,844
And Kyun, you can relax.

491
00:21:18,910 --> 00:21:22,381
Kyun? Right, your Korean name is Kyun.

492
00:21:22,447 --> 00:21:23,749
-Lee Kyun.
-Lee Kyun.

493
00:21:24,349 --> 00:21:25,284
Doing okay, Kyun?

494
00:21:25,350 --> 00:21:26,718
Yes, Kyun is doing okay.

495
00:21:28,186 --> 00:21:30,722
-I was born in October.
-October.

496
00:21:30,789 --> 00:21:34,359
The younger-looking guy
born in the Year of the Mouse.

497
00:21:34,426 --> 00:21:36,495
I still find it hard
to speak casually to him.

498
00:21:36,561 --> 00:21:38,563
-My bro, Kyun, is fun.
-Kyun is fun.

499
00:21:38,630 --> 00:21:41,500
-He has a great voice.
-He does.

500
00:21:41,566 --> 00:21:45,404
And now, you're watching
the return of <i>Chef & My Fridge</i>.

501
00:21:45,470 --> 00:21:47,172
Let us decide the contenders

502
00:21:47,239 --> 00:21:49,875
-before we open the fridges.
-Gosh.

503
00:21:49,941 --> 00:21:51,810
-We'll decide on the contenders.
-The contenders.

504
00:21:51,877 --> 00:21:56,148
We're yet to find out
what ingredients are in the fridges.

505
00:21:56,214 --> 00:21:59,251
What kind of dishes do they want to eat?

506
00:21:59,318 --> 00:22:02,454
Please show us their order.

507
00:22:02,521 --> 00:22:04,289
Here is Youngtak's order.

508
00:22:04,356 --> 00:22:06,325
YOUNGTAK'S ORDER

509
00:22:06,391 --> 00:22:07,926
Here's Youngtak's order.

510
00:22:07,993 --> 00:22:11,330
<i>This is where Tak gets his power</i>

511
00:22:11,396 --> 00:22:14,933
<i>This is where Tak gets his power</i>

512
00:22:15,000 --> 00:22:17,235
-We need you to elaborate.
-First of all,

513
00:22:17,302 --> 00:22:21,606
I came here after my concert
in Gangneung yesterday.

514
00:22:21,673 --> 00:22:22,974
-Are you on a tour?
-Yes.

515
00:22:23,041 --> 00:22:24,776
And because I'm on a tour,

516
00:22:24,843 --> 00:22:27,779
I want to eat something
that will recharge my energy.

517
00:22:27,846 --> 00:22:32,384
If you'd make me something like that,
I'd eat everything with gratitude.

518
00:22:32,451 --> 00:22:33,752
So what's your order again?

519
00:22:33,819 --> 00:22:37,122
<i>This is where Tak gets his power</i>

520
00:22:37,189 --> 00:22:38,223
I suddenly got excited.

521
00:22:38,290 --> 00:22:41,026
-He's different from you.
-Very much, right?

522
00:22:41,093 --> 00:22:42,594
HANG IN THERE, SUNG-JU

523
00:22:42,661 --> 00:22:45,163
That's the first order,
and then there's egg paradise.

524
00:22:45,230 --> 00:22:46,565
Egg paradise?

525
00:22:46,631 --> 00:22:50,235
While I couldn't make enough money,

526
00:22:50,302 --> 00:22:52,204
I'd always buy eggs first.

527
00:22:52,270 --> 00:22:58,043
So I want to eat an egg dish
that'll give me a taste of paradise.

528
00:22:58,110 --> 00:23:00,178
<i>Culinary Class Wars</i> had
a tofu hell mission.

529
00:23:00,245 --> 00:23:02,080
-Tofu hell.
-Yes, there was tofu hell.

530
00:23:02,147 --> 00:23:05,016
But today, he wants egg paradise.

531
00:23:05,083 --> 00:23:10,389
Let us decide on the contenders
who'll cook for Youngtak.

532
00:23:10,455 --> 00:23:13,291
He may have lots of ingredients or not.

533
00:23:13,358 --> 00:23:18,597
But if any of you are up for the challenge
and want to cook for him, let us know.

534
00:23:20,132 --> 00:23:21,700
-I'll try.
-Sorry?

535
00:23:21,767 --> 00:23:24,202
I want to give Youngtak some energy.

536
00:23:24,269 --> 00:23:26,471
You want to give him some energy.

537
00:23:26,538 --> 00:23:28,140
Can you sing that line?

538
00:23:28,206 --> 00:23:30,709
<i>This is where Tak gets his power</i>

539
00:23:30,776 --> 00:23:34,246
<i>This is where Tak gets his power</i>

540
00:23:34,312 --> 00:23:36,114
-The trot song.
-He puts his name down.

541
00:23:36,181 --> 00:23:37,582
Lee Yeon-bok's name is down.

542
00:23:37,649 --> 00:23:40,819
In that case…
Whoever that calls it will get it.

543
00:23:40,886 --> 00:23:42,621
-It's better to get over with it.
-One of the three

544
00:23:42,687 --> 00:23:44,489
-must go to egg paradise.
-Yes.

545
00:23:44,556 --> 00:23:47,592
I'll also take Youngtak's fridge.

546
00:23:47,659 --> 00:23:49,661
-You'll choose his fridge?
-Yes.

547
00:23:49,728 --> 00:23:51,930
Which theme do you want?

548
00:23:51,997 --> 00:23:53,064
The upper one.

549
00:23:53,131 --> 00:23:55,233
-The upper one?
-This is where Tak gets his power?

550
00:23:55,300 --> 00:23:57,002
Can you… One, two, three, four.

551
00:23:57,068 --> 00:23:58,270
GIGGLING

552
00:23:58,336 --> 00:24:00,605
You have to sing it to take that round.

553
00:24:00,672 --> 00:24:02,574
Don't make the chefs sing.

554
00:24:02,641 --> 00:24:03,809
She has to do it.

555
00:24:03,875 --> 00:24:05,377
-One, two, three, four.
-Three, four.

556
00:24:05,444 --> 00:24:08,046
<i>Real, real, real, real, the real deal</i>

557
00:24:08,113 --> 00:24:10,415
That's a different song.

558
00:24:10,482 --> 00:24:14,419
-I don't know that song.
-You don't know the song?

559
00:24:14,486 --> 00:24:15,554
Chef Kang-rok.

560
00:24:15,620 --> 00:24:17,622
-Yes?
-If you sing well, you can take it.

561
00:24:17,689 --> 00:24:19,191
Sing? I can't sing. No.

562
00:24:19,257 --> 00:24:20,459
ANSWERING FASTER THAN EVER

563
00:24:20,525 --> 00:24:22,727
Wouldn't it be better to get it over with?

564
00:24:22,794 --> 00:24:24,663
-Let me watch for a moment.
-He wants to watch.

565
00:24:24,729 --> 00:24:26,731
-The audience mode.
-He's cautious.

566
00:24:26,798 --> 00:24:30,202
Chef Mi-yeong decides to cook
a stamina dish.

567
00:24:30,268 --> 00:24:33,205
-Korean cuisine is mostly healthy.
-It's the best.

568
00:24:33,271 --> 00:24:34,139
-I'll try.
-Great.

569
00:24:34,206 --> 00:24:38,610
Now, Chef Mi-yeong is
competing against Chef Yeon-bok.

570
00:24:38,677 --> 00:24:39,678
The two masters.

571
00:24:39,744 --> 00:24:43,448
-Next one is egg paradise.
-This won't be easy.

572
00:24:43,515 --> 00:24:45,951
Everyone is looking around.

573
00:24:46,017 --> 00:24:47,285
Poong, aren't eggs better for you?

574
00:24:47,352 --> 00:24:49,488
I can go between paradise and hell.

575
00:24:49,554 --> 00:24:51,423
I'll do it.

576
00:24:51,490 --> 00:24:53,325
-Gosh, thank you.
-Chef Hyun-suk.

577
00:24:53,391 --> 00:24:56,228
I'll give you a taste of paradise

578
00:24:56,294 --> 00:24:58,597
by using eggs.

579
00:24:58,663 --> 00:25:01,867
-All right, Hyun-suk to egg paradise.
-To egg paradise.

580
00:25:02,434 --> 00:25:04,402
And now, the… Whoa.

581
00:25:04,469 --> 00:25:07,339
Edward?

582
00:25:07,405 --> 00:25:08,740
-Really?
-He pushed it.

583
00:25:08,807 --> 00:25:14,546
Because I wanted to battle Hyun-suk.

584
00:25:14,613 --> 00:25:17,249
He wants to battle with Hyun-suk.

585
00:25:17,315 --> 00:25:18,583
I will…

586
00:25:18,650 --> 00:25:21,253
<i>Let's go to egg paradise</i>

587
00:25:21,319 --> 00:25:24,623
LEE KYUN SLAYED

588
00:25:24,689 --> 00:25:26,625
-Egg paradise.
-Yes.

589
00:25:26,691 --> 00:25:27,692
He didn't have to do it.

590
00:25:27,759 --> 00:25:32,597
Youngtak wanted to taste your food,
so he goes to egg paradise.

591
00:25:32,664 --> 00:25:35,667
<i>Let's go to egg paradise</i>

592
00:25:35,734 --> 00:25:37,536
That sounds great.

593
00:25:37,602 --> 00:25:41,106
Chef Edward chooses egg paradise.

594
00:25:41,172 --> 00:25:43,008
This is a huge match.

595
00:25:43,074 --> 00:25:45,243
THE BATTLE OF PRIDE
BETWEEN TWO FRIENDS

596
00:25:45,310 --> 00:25:47,245
COMING RIGHT UP

597
00:25:47,312 --> 00:25:50,282
This round is a battle

598
00:25:50,348 --> 00:25:53,919
between the two hottest chefs
both born in the year 1972.

599
00:25:53,985 --> 00:25:58,123
Choi Hyun-suk is such a great chef.

600
00:25:58,189 --> 00:26:00,292
I'll show you how fun cooking can be

601
00:26:00,358 --> 00:26:02,727
even without salt performances
and comical relief.

602
00:26:05,597 --> 00:26:07,098
Hey, it's on fire!

603
00:26:07,165 --> 00:26:08,300
Fire.

604
00:26:08,366 --> 00:26:09,634
It's ruined.

605
00:26:09,701 --> 00:26:11,202
The eggs are burning!

606
00:26:11,269 --> 00:26:12,604
<i>You burnt it</i>

607
00:26:12,671 --> 00:26:15,373
<i>Jingle, jingle, jingle, jingle</i>
<i>You burnt it</i>

608
00:26:15,440 --> 00:26:17,375
THE TWO CHEFS' FIERY BATTLE

609
00:26:17,876 --> 00:26:22,781
Now, it's time to take a peek
into Youngtak's fridge.

610
00:26:22,847 --> 00:26:25,483
-You're wearing gloves?
-Yes.

611
00:26:25,550 --> 00:26:27,619
-Yes, we have to.
-The gloves are here.

612
00:26:27,686 --> 00:26:29,387
I can't believe I'm seeing this.

613
00:26:29,454 --> 00:26:32,090
We always keep things sanitary.

614
00:26:32,157 --> 00:26:33,825
PLEASE DO YOUR BEST FOR ME

615
00:26:33,892 --> 00:26:35,727
Is this the fridge you have at home?

616
00:26:35,794 --> 00:26:38,964
Not the fridge itself, though.
My fridge is a built-in.

617
00:26:39,030 --> 00:26:42,233
-But everything inside is mine.
-The contents.

618
00:26:42,300 --> 00:26:44,402
We always make sure
we empty out everything.

619
00:26:44,469 --> 00:26:45,403
YOUNGTAK'S FRIDGE, COMING UP

620
00:26:45,470 --> 00:26:48,940
We present Youngtak's fridge.

621
00:26:49,007 --> 00:26:51,309
WHAT'S YOUNGTAK'S FRIDGE LIKE?

622
00:26:51,376 --> 00:26:52,510
This is it.

623
00:26:54,346 --> 00:26:55,747
This is it.

624
00:26:55,814 --> 00:26:58,817
He has quite a lot of things.

625
00:26:58,883 --> 00:27:01,186
The freezer is completely empty.

626
00:27:01,252 --> 00:27:03,622
-It's pretty empty.
-There isn't much.

627
00:27:03,688 --> 00:27:06,591
It looks rather empty.

628
00:27:06,658 --> 00:27:08,593
CAN'T BELIEVE HIS EYES

629
00:27:08,660 --> 00:27:11,162
-There's nothing.
-He has nothing.

630
00:27:11,229 --> 00:27:14,232
The first thing
that captured my eyes was eggs.

631
00:27:14,299 --> 00:27:16,034
He already had three.

632
00:27:16,101 --> 00:27:17,535
You need to make do with these.

633
00:27:17,602 --> 00:27:21,806
-Egg paradise, Chef Hyun-suk and Edward.
-He has 12.

634
00:27:21,873 --> 00:27:23,808
He has red pepper powder.

635
00:27:23,875 --> 00:27:25,276
Do you like spicy food?

636
00:27:25,343 --> 00:27:27,946
I had been holding it back recently.

637
00:27:28,013 --> 00:27:30,682
I'd look puffy when I ate spicy food.

638
00:27:30,749 --> 00:27:31,916
You can look puffy.

639
00:27:31,983 --> 00:27:34,185
But I'll let myself go today.

640
00:27:34,252 --> 00:27:35,420
I want something spicy.

641
00:27:35,487 --> 00:27:37,522
So did you always like spicy food?

642
00:27:37,589 --> 00:27:41,459
There's that extra-spicy brand
of <i>tteokbokki</i>, right? I eat it as is.

643
00:27:41,526 --> 00:27:45,130
-He already has veggies ready to go.
-He does.

644
00:27:45,196 --> 00:27:47,098
He has radish and pumpkin.

645
00:27:47,165 --> 00:27:47,999
These are all prepped.

646
00:27:48,066 --> 00:27:51,569
I rarely cook at home,
so my mother leaves those.

647
00:27:51,636 --> 00:27:53,805
It's a meal prep by your mother.

648
00:27:53,872 --> 00:27:55,540
She leaves them prepped?

649
00:27:55,607 --> 00:27:57,308
-So you can heat and eat it?
-Yes.

650
00:27:57,375 --> 00:28:00,578
My mother makes excellent <i>chogochujang</i>.

651
00:28:00,645 --> 00:28:03,214
-She must have a secret.
-His mother's <i>chogochujang</i>.

652
00:28:03,281 --> 00:28:05,717
Following his mother's <i>chogochujang</i> is
raw oysters.

653
00:28:05,784 --> 00:28:07,185
I love oysters.

654
00:28:07,252 --> 00:28:08,486
They're in season now.

655
00:28:08,553 --> 00:28:10,522
Edward, check how fresh it is.

656
00:28:10,588 --> 00:28:12,190
These are expensive overseas.

657
00:28:12,257 --> 00:28:14,526
-He's eating it with a spoon.
-Like that.

658
00:28:14,592 --> 00:28:15,860
You just had a big bite.

659
00:28:15,927 --> 00:28:18,063
Kyun, aren't you eating a little too much?

660
00:28:19,330 --> 00:28:20,699
He wants to taste <i>chogochujang</i> too.

661
00:28:20,765 --> 00:28:23,134
-He's ready to dine.
-He is.

662
00:28:23,201 --> 00:28:25,303
He got a big dip of the sauce.

663
00:28:25,370 --> 00:28:27,305
It's delicious.

664
00:28:27,372 --> 00:28:28,740
He approved of this.

665
00:28:28,807 --> 00:28:31,042
-She's really good.
-His mother is an expert.

666
00:28:31,109 --> 00:28:32,911
-I found kimchi.
-Kimchi.

667
00:28:32,977 --> 00:28:34,946
His mother must've made these.

668
00:28:35,013 --> 00:28:36,781
-And bulgogi.
-That looks so good.

669
00:28:36,848 --> 00:28:39,918
I can't cook,
so she makes it easy for me to eat.

670
00:28:39,984 --> 00:28:41,753
You have to taste this one.

671
00:28:41,820 --> 00:28:44,022
This one? Raw?

672
00:28:44,089 --> 00:28:45,290
IT'S FOR OUR CHEFS

673
00:28:45,356 --> 00:28:46,725
Are you crazy?

674
00:28:46,791 --> 00:28:49,160
-How can I…
-They need to know how salty it is.

675
00:28:49,227 --> 00:28:52,464
Hey, you've improved a lot.
You learned to make me do things.

676
00:28:52,530 --> 00:28:55,734
-I've returned after five years.
-Goodness, kiddo.

677
00:28:55,800 --> 00:28:57,102
I'll mess with you.

678
00:28:57,168 --> 00:28:58,103
LAUGHING OUT LOUD

679
00:28:58,169 --> 00:29:00,138
Finally. What is this?

680
00:29:00,205 --> 00:29:02,340
I finally found fish.

681
00:29:02,407 --> 00:29:04,676
-Fish.
-Fish? Seafood?

682
00:29:05,243 --> 00:29:07,479
I LOVE FISH

683
00:29:07,545 --> 00:29:10,582
-I found <i>bakdae</i>.
-<i>Bakdae</i>. Yes.

684
00:29:10,648 --> 00:29:13,518
-Crabs.
-We found crabs. These are ready too.

685
00:29:13,585 --> 00:29:15,787
-Octopus.
-Yes, that's an octopus.

686
00:29:15,854 --> 00:29:17,655
I think I prefer seafood.

687
00:29:17,722 --> 00:29:20,058
He leans more toward seafood.

688
00:29:20,125 --> 00:29:21,860
That was all for Youngtak's fridge.

689
00:29:21,926 --> 00:29:25,730
This is the opening round
of the new <i>Chef & My Fridge</i>.

690
00:29:25,797 --> 00:29:28,800
IT'S FINALLY BEGINNING

691
00:29:28,867 --> 00:29:32,070
We give a star badge to the winner.

692
00:29:32,137 --> 00:29:36,574
The owner of the fridge will
give a star to the winning chef.

693
00:29:36,641 --> 00:29:37,742
A STAR FROM THE OWNER

694
00:29:37,809 --> 00:29:42,781
And now, let us begin the round
between Chef Yeon-bok and Chef Mi-yeong.

695
00:29:42,847 --> 00:29:45,083
You're watching the return
of <i>Chef & My Fridge,</i>

696
00:29:45,150 --> 00:29:47,552
-and let us watch the opening match.
-The opening match?

697
00:29:47,619 --> 00:29:51,356
Let the best chef win
the title of the master chef.

698
00:29:51,422 --> 00:29:53,591
Master of School Meals, Chef Lee Mi-yeong,

699
00:29:53,658 --> 00:29:57,362
versus Master of Chinese Cuisine,
Chef Lee Yeon-bok.

700
00:29:58,496 --> 00:30:01,432
Before we begin the actual round,

701
00:30:01,499 --> 00:30:03,568
I have an urgent announcement.

702
00:30:03,635 --> 00:30:07,238
The new <i>Chef & My Fridge</i>
also has a new rule.

703
00:30:07,305 --> 00:30:10,241
-We're giving out hidden perks.
-What?

704
00:30:10,308 --> 00:30:14,312
Because this is a battle
between returning chefs and new chefs,

705
00:30:14,379 --> 00:30:17,982
the new chefs may find it unfamiliar
to cook within 15 minutes.

706
00:30:18,049 --> 00:30:21,286
So we wish to provide trivial perks.

707
00:30:21,352 --> 00:30:23,321
-What could it be?
-What is it?

708
00:30:23,388 --> 00:30:24,489
DELIGHTED

709
00:30:24,556 --> 00:30:27,959
-You may choose one of the two.
-What are the options?

710
00:30:28,026 --> 00:30:30,261
-There are options.
-Options?

711
00:30:30,328 --> 00:30:32,397
The first perk is

712
00:30:32,463 --> 00:30:38,436
starting one minute earlier.

713
00:30:38,503 --> 00:30:39,337
-A minute?
-A minute?

714
00:30:39,404 --> 00:30:42,640
-They get 16 minutes?
-To be exact, they get 16 minutes.

715
00:30:42,707 --> 00:30:45,343
-A minute on this show is huge.
-It's significant.

716
00:30:45,410 --> 00:30:49,581
The first option is to start
one minute before the returning chef.

717
00:30:49,647 --> 00:30:51,482
The second perk is

718
00:30:51,549 --> 00:30:55,486
-stopping for a minute.
-Stopping for a minute?

719
00:30:55,553 --> 00:30:58,156
Whenever the new chef makes the call,

720
00:30:58,223 --> 00:31:02,660
-the other chef must stop for a minute.
-What is this?

721
00:31:02,727 --> 00:31:03,862
What is this?

722
00:31:03,928 --> 00:31:05,897
-Must stop for a minute.
-What is this?

723
00:31:05,964 --> 00:31:07,498
A VERY TRIVIAL PERK

724
00:31:07,565 --> 00:31:08,766
Hey, wait a minute.

725
00:31:08,833 --> 00:31:11,502
-Are you telling us to stop our hands?
-Yes.

726
00:31:11,569 --> 00:31:13,037
You have to keep it under control.

727
00:31:15,039 --> 00:31:18,343
This means
the new chefs get all 15 minutes,

728
00:31:18,409 --> 00:31:22,080
while the returning chefs get
only 14 minutes.

729
00:31:22,146 --> 00:31:24,382
-Did you say 14 minutes?
-You must stop for 1 minute.

730
00:31:24,449 --> 00:31:27,485
-So 14 minutes?
-You don't get that 1 minute.

731
00:31:27,552 --> 00:31:30,922
Wait, the 15-minute rule is
the foundation of <i>Chef & My Fridge</i>.

732
00:31:32,523 --> 00:31:33,825
It's our foundation.

733
00:31:33,892 --> 00:31:38,096
However, you cannot use it
once the five-minute interim check begins.

734
00:31:39,097 --> 00:31:42,533
You can't use it in the last five minutes,
so use it in the first ten.

735
00:31:42,600 --> 00:31:43,801
Yes, that'll be serious.

736
00:31:43,868 --> 00:31:48,172
If the new chefs don't want to use it,
you don't have to use the perks.

737
00:31:48,239 --> 00:31:49,641
I have a feeling

738
00:31:49,707 --> 00:31:51,009
Kyun wouldn't do that

739
00:31:51,075 --> 00:31:53,478
because he likes to play fair
in the same situation.

740
00:31:53,544 --> 00:31:56,481
-He wouldn't want to use it.
-No.

741
00:31:56,547 --> 00:31:58,416
Chef Edward was the one

742
00:31:58,483 --> 00:32:02,420
who showed the biggest smile
when I explained this rule.

743
00:32:02,487 --> 00:32:04,122
This is… Gosh.

744
00:32:04,188 --> 00:32:06,090
Do you like the hidden perks?

745
00:32:06,157 --> 00:32:09,527
-Yes, it's wonderful.
-It's wonderful!

746
00:32:09,594 --> 00:32:11,129
Isn't it?

747
00:32:11,195 --> 00:32:14,098
Why don't we take 15 minutes
and they all get 16 minutes?

748
00:32:14,165 --> 00:32:15,800
If you don't feel confident,

749
00:32:15,867 --> 00:32:17,435
-please leave.
-Just leave.

750
00:32:18,736 --> 00:32:21,406
Why have you developed
a habit of making excuses?

751
00:32:21,472 --> 00:32:24,742
-It's you, Choi Hyun-suk.
-You're all returning chefs. Come on.

752
00:32:24,809 --> 00:32:26,411
Why won't you accept this?

753
00:32:26,477 --> 00:32:30,515
Chief Mi-yeong, will you use your perk?

754
00:32:30,581 --> 00:32:31,482
WHAT WILL SHE DO?

755
00:32:31,549 --> 00:32:35,186
-Will you use your perk?
-Yes.

756
00:32:35,253 --> 00:32:36,955
She will use it.

757
00:32:37,021 --> 00:32:38,690
-You can choose one of the two.
-Yes.

758
00:32:38,756 --> 00:32:42,593
-I'll start a minute early.
-She'll start a minute early.

759
00:32:42,660 --> 00:32:44,295
She'll begin a minute early.

760
00:32:44,362 --> 00:32:45,830
Is that okay, Chef Yeon-bok?

761
00:32:45,897 --> 00:32:48,666
-So what if I'm not okay with it?
-So what?

762
00:32:48,733 --> 00:32:50,368
We just wanted your opinion.

763
00:32:50,435 --> 00:32:52,637
-Okay.
-All right.

764
00:32:52,704 --> 00:32:56,307
-That's a master chef.
-He gladly said okay.

765
00:32:56,374 --> 00:32:59,143
Chef Mi-yeong, from what I heard,

766
00:32:59,210 --> 00:33:01,346
you were a bit disappointed

767
00:33:01,412 --> 00:33:04,182
because Chef Yeon-bok took
all the ingredients you wanted.

768
00:33:04,248 --> 00:33:07,051
-Really? Wait, his side is full.
-I just got that intel.

769
00:33:07,118 --> 00:33:09,320
-Great job.
-He took

770
00:33:09,387 --> 00:33:12,323
all the ingredients like he's hazing her.

771
00:33:12,390 --> 00:33:15,693
-I'll share it with her. I'll be fair.
-We'll share.

772
00:33:15,760 --> 00:33:17,862
-Do it now.
-Stop making me look evil.

773
00:33:17,929 --> 00:33:19,364
-It looked like you were hazing her.
-Yes.

774
00:33:19,430 --> 00:33:21,833
-I heard you took the octopus.
-No.

775
00:33:21,899 --> 00:33:24,669
You have to share it.
You need to grab it quickly.

776
00:33:24,736 --> 00:33:27,972
May we sell the ingredients
in exchange for time?

777
00:33:29,674 --> 00:33:32,477
What you said was something
that shakes our very foundation.

778
00:33:32,543 --> 00:33:35,780
-Go back to <i>Culinary Class Wars</i>.
-What are you saying?

779
00:33:35,847 --> 00:33:39,984
I didn't want 1 minute.
I just wanted 30 seconds.

780
00:33:40,051 --> 00:33:43,021
-Two pieces. Thank you.
-Two pieces?

781
00:33:43,588 --> 00:33:46,457
SPLIT UP FAIRLY

782
00:33:47,392 --> 00:33:48,760
CHEF LEE MI-YEONG'S INGREDIENTS

783
00:33:48,826 --> 00:33:50,194
KIMCHI, OCTOPUS, RADISH,
SHISHITO PEPPER, BROTH PACK,

784
00:33:50,261 --> 00:33:51,796
STARCH SYRUP, COOKING WINE
SESAME OIL, SPICY PEPPER POWDER,

785
00:33:51,863 --> 00:33:52,730
PLUM SYRUP,
TUNA SAUCE, RED PEPPER

786
00:33:52,797 --> 00:33:54,899
The theme of your dishes is…

787
00:33:54,966 --> 00:33:58,302
<i>This is where Tak gets his power</i>

788
00:33:58,369 --> 00:34:02,006
You'll have to make stamina food.
I wonder what you plan to make.

789
00:34:02,073 --> 00:34:04,509
I want to make braised octopus and kimchi…

790
00:34:04,575 --> 00:34:09,714
<i>Real, real, real, real, real good</i>

791
00:34:09,781 --> 00:34:11,182
What did you say?

792
00:34:12,417 --> 00:34:13,484
-What?
-Octopus, kimchi, what?

793
00:34:13,551 --> 00:34:15,553
Braised octopus and kimchi…

794
00:34:15,620 --> 00:34:18,089
<i>Real, real, real, real, real good</i>

795
00:34:18,156 --> 00:34:20,058
DOING HER BEST TO SING

796
00:34:20,124 --> 00:34:21,092
This is awkward.

797
00:34:21,159 --> 00:34:24,095
<i>Real, real, real, real, real good</i>

798
00:34:24,162 --> 00:34:25,763
CHEF LEE MI-YEONG: REAL GOOD
BRAISED OCTOPUS AND KIMCHI

799
00:34:25,830 --> 00:34:29,267
<i>It's real good, octopus</i>

800
00:34:29,333 --> 00:34:31,903
Octopus is an ingredient
that gives you stamina, right?

801
00:34:31,969 --> 00:34:36,174
I want to throw in ripe kimchi
and make a spicy braised dish.

802
00:34:36,240 --> 00:34:40,078
You said you liked spicy food,
so I'll make a delicious dish for you.

803
00:34:40,144 --> 00:34:44,348
Also, shishito peppers and doenjang sauce
and shredded radish salad.

804
00:34:44,415 --> 00:34:47,218
-Koreans need rice, right?
-Yes.

805
00:34:47,285 --> 00:34:50,721
-I'll make a whole meal for your energy.
-Is this…

806
00:34:50,788 --> 00:34:53,324
Can she really make everything
in 15 minutes?

807
00:34:53,391 --> 00:34:54,559
Can you do it?

808
00:34:54,625 --> 00:34:55,860
Yes, it's all for Youngtak.

809
00:34:55,927 --> 00:34:57,862
-It's all for Youngtak.
-Yes.

810
00:34:57,929 --> 00:34:58,996
All right.

811
00:34:59,831 --> 00:35:01,666
CHEF LEE YEON-BOK'S INGREDIENTS

812
00:35:01,732 --> 00:35:03,534
OCTOPUS, CRAB, BEEF BULGOGI,
BROTH PACK, ONION, ZUCCHINI

813
00:35:03,601 --> 00:35:05,470
GOCHUJANG, TUNA SAUCE,
SOY SAUCE, SPICY PEPPER POWDER

814
00:35:05,536 --> 00:35:08,272
-My dish is called Bok Show.
-Bok Show?

815
00:35:08,339 --> 00:35:10,441
-Bok Show? With your name?
-Bok Show?

816
00:35:10,508 --> 00:35:12,543
His current tour is called Tak Show.

817
00:35:12,610 --> 00:35:16,280
-Yes.
-So I'll make special <i>tteokbokki</i>.

818
00:35:16,347 --> 00:35:18,049
-Bok is in <i>tteokbokki</i> too.
-I'll also make the rice cake.

819
00:35:18,116 --> 00:35:19,217
You'll make rice cake?

820
00:35:19,283 --> 00:35:23,454
I'll also make dumplings
and put it up as a side.

821
00:35:23,521 --> 00:35:25,623
I'll put in everything I know

822
00:35:25,690 --> 00:35:29,360
-from my experience of <i>Chef & My Fridge</i>.
-I see.

823
00:35:29,427 --> 00:35:31,496
Tak will eat that and sing…

824
00:35:31,562 --> 00:35:34,031
<i>This is where Tak gets his power</i>

825
00:35:34,098 --> 00:35:35,233
THIS IS WHERE TAK GETS HIS POWER

826
00:35:35,299 --> 00:35:37,001
AMAZED

827
00:35:37,068 --> 00:35:39,770
-He's serious about trot songs.
-He's a good singer.

828
00:35:39,837 --> 00:35:42,974
And now,
the return of <i>Chef & My Fridge</i> will

829
00:35:43,040 --> 00:35:46,043
begin the long-awaited opening match.

830
00:35:47,345 --> 00:35:49,013
Look at the pin lights.

831
00:35:49,080 --> 00:35:50,081
CHEF LEE MI-YEONG VS
CHEF LEE YEON-BOK

832
00:35:50,148 --> 00:35:52,150
Look at the pin lights.

833
00:35:52,216 --> 00:35:53,518
Looking great!

834
00:35:53,584 --> 00:35:55,119
Gosh, I'm nervous.

835
00:35:55,186 --> 00:35:56,621
-It's been so long.
-Everyone gets nervous.

836
00:35:57,321 --> 00:35:58,789
It's the most nerve-racking moment.

837
00:35:58,856 --> 00:36:00,391
I can't believe I'm here in person.

838
00:36:01,192 --> 00:36:02,026
They're right there.

839
00:36:02,693 --> 00:36:03,861
RACING HEART

840
00:36:03,928 --> 00:36:07,165
The most winning chef of <i>Chef & My Fridge</i>,

841
00:36:07,231 --> 00:36:10,034
the master of Chinese cuisine,
Chef Lee Yeon-bok is

842
00:36:10,101 --> 00:36:13,771
up against the master of school meals,
Chef Lee Mi-yeong,

843
00:36:13,838 --> 00:36:17,508
who seized the appetite of young children
and a Michelin restaurant chef.

844
00:36:17,575 --> 00:36:22,079
Who will defend their title as the master?

845
00:36:22,146 --> 00:36:26,150
Chef Mi-yeong chose
to begin one minute earlier.

846
00:36:26,217 --> 00:36:28,986
You may begin one minute earlier.

847
00:36:29,053 --> 00:36:31,455
THE ROUND BEGINS
1 MINUTE EARLIER!

848
00:36:32,823 --> 00:36:34,458
She has one minute.

849
00:36:34,525 --> 00:36:35,593
You may begin one minute earlier.

850
00:36:35,660 --> 00:36:38,829
Chef Mi-yeong goes straight to the stove.

851
00:36:38,896 --> 00:36:42,667
-She has one minute.
-She's starting.

852
00:36:42,733 --> 00:36:45,636
I think
she's boiling something in the pot.

853
00:36:45,703 --> 00:36:47,338
-A minute is critical.
-What's inside?

854
00:36:47,405 --> 00:36:48,839
-Water.
-Water.

855
00:36:48,906 --> 00:36:51,108
-I'm going to make broth.
-Broth.

856
00:36:51,175 --> 00:36:52,810
Is it for the braised octopus?

857
00:36:52,877 --> 00:36:54,679
-Broth?
-She seems too at ease.

858
00:36:54,745 --> 00:36:55,813
She seems at ease.

859
00:36:55,880 --> 00:36:57,982
-It's for the braised kimchi.
-She spent 20 seconds.

860
00:36:58,049 --> 00:36:59,850
-Has seconds always been that fast?
-Yes.

861
00:36:59,917 --> 00:37:02,353
-Why is the time flying?
-Yes, seriously.

862
00:37:03,020 --> 00:37:05,256
-Twenty seconds have passed.
-Time is flying by.

863
00:37:05,323 --> 00:37:07,325
Have you ever had
braised octopus and kimchi?

864
00:37:07,391 --> 00:37:09,126
-It's a first.
-It's my first too.

865
00:37:09,193 --> 00:37:11,562
We often eat stir-fried octopus.

866
00:37:11,629 --> 00:37:13,264
Octopus in braised kimchi?

867
00:37:13,331 --> 00:37:15,900
And because she began a minute earlier,

868
00:37:15,967 --> 00:37:19,036
-she ends up getting everyone's attention.
-That's a lot of pressure.

869
00:37:19,103 --> 00:37:20,805
This isn't easy.

870
00:37:20,871 --> 00:37:26,244
It must be nerve-racking
to get everyone's attention.

871
00:37:26,310 --> 00:37:28,446
She's working on shishito peppers.

872
00:37:28,512 --> 00:37:31,882
After all, her main dish is
braised octopus and kimchi.

873
00:37:31,949 --> 00:37:33,884
She could do shishito peppers later.

874
00:37:33,951 --> 00:37:35,920
-I want to get the vegetables ready.
-A minute…

875
00:37:35,987 --> 00:37:37,955
-Ten. Nine.
-Nine.

876
00:37:38,022 --> 00:37:39,924
-Eight. Seven.
-Eight. Seven.

877
00:37:39,991 --> 00:37:41,826
-Six. Five.
-Six. Five.

878
00:37:41,892 --> 00:37:43,628
-Four. Three.
-Four. Three.

879
00:37:43,694 --> 00:37:45,329
-Two. One.
-Two. One.

880
00:37:45,396 --> 00:37:49,433
And now,
the 15-minute cooking match begins!

881
00:37:49,500 --> 00:37:51,969
-All right!
-Chef Yeon-bok begins.

882
00:37:52,036 --> 00:37:54,238
Chef Yeon-bok can cook too.

883
00:37:54,305 --> 00:37:56,507
A minute is such a short amount of time.

884
00:37:56,574 --> 00:37:58,976
Chef Yeon-bok also begins
by starting the fire.

885
00:37:59,043 --> 00:38:01,145
BOK SHOW: ADD BROTH PACK
AND OCTOPUS TO MAKE BROTH

886
00:38:01,212 --> 00:38:02,213
MAKING THE DOUGH RIGHT AWAY

887
00:38:02,280 --> 00:38:03,981
He's making the dough now.

888
00:38:04,048 --> 00:38:06,884
It looks like Chef Yeon-bok is
making rice cake for <i>tteokbokki</i>.

889
00:38:06,951 --> 00:38:08,519
He's making flour cake, not rice cake.

890
00:38:08,586 --> 00:38:09,920
-Oh, flour cake.
-Flour cake.

891
00:38:10,988 --> 00:38:13,624
-Did he throw in hot water?
-Yes, hot dough.

892
00:38:13,691 --> 00:38:15,860
He added hot water
to flour and salt to make dough.

893
00:38:15,926 --> 00:38:16,927
A dough, I see.

894
00:38:16,994 --> 00:38:19,096
HOT WATER HELPS IT COOK
EVEN AS IT RISES

895
00:38:24,168 --> 00:38:27,138
Using hot water will
help you make the dough faster.

896
00:38:27,204 --> 00:38:28,272
HE QUICKLY FINISHES THE DOUGH

897
00:38:28,339 --> 00:38:31,742
There's the kimchi.
Chef Mi-yeong gets the kimchi.

898
00:38:32,777 --> 00:38:34,645
GASP!

899
00:38:35,346 --> 00:38:37,081
A BIT FLUSTERED WITH THE KIMCHI

900
00:38:37,148 --> 00:38:40,685
I didn't know the kimchi would be

901
00:38:40,751 --> 00:38:42,820
cut into pieces all the way through.

902
00:38:42,887 --> 00:38:46,123
-You have to cook as you speak!
-Yes.

903
00:38:46,190 --> 00:38:47,625
She was busy explaining.

904
00:38:47,692 --> 00:38:49,327
-This isn't a talk show.
-All of a sudden?

905
00:38:49,393 --> 00:38:52,330
-I thought it was a recipe show.
-Right?

906
00:38:52,396 --> 00:38:54,398
-My mother has a habit
-She hid it.

907
00:38:54,465 --> 00:38:58,202
of cutting up the insides
and covering it with a big leaf.

908
00:38:58,269 --> 00:39:00,905
She was deceived by how it looked!

909
00:39:00,971 --> 00:39:05,009
That's why you should
always check the ingredients first.

910
00:39:05,076 --> 00:39:07,378
This is like a nightmare.

911
00:39:07,445 --> 00:39:11,182
-The kimchi.
-Yes, after all, it's braised kimchi.

912
00:39:11,248 --> 00:39:15,186
-She just put it in with the broth pack.
-She just threw it in.

913
00:39:15,252 --> 00:39:17,988
-Is that okay? The broth pack?
-Is that okay?

914
00:39:18,055 --> 00:39:21,525
-Is that okay, Chef Mi-yeong?
-Yes, it's fine.

915
00:39:21,592 --> 00:39:23,294
She was firm.

916
00:39:24,795 --> 00:39:27,498
She's even washing the dishes,
a rare sight on <i>Chef & My Fridge</i>.

917
00:39:27,565 --> 00:39:29,233
She should just cook.

918
00:39:29,300 --> 00:39:33,704
-She's wiping the board and washing it.
-She's doing that? I've never seen it.

919
00:39:33,771 --> 00:39:34,972
She's the master of school meals.

920
00:39:35,039 --> 00:39:37,641
-She probably has no time.
-That was a rare sight.

921
00:39:37,708 --> 00:39:39,176
It was.

922
00:39:39,243 --> 00:39:42,046
-It's not easy to clean up as you cook.
-No.

923
00:39:42,113 --> 00:39:43,414
She's cutting up radish.

924
00:39:43,481 --> 00:39:45,583
Let's take a look. Yes.

925
00:39:45,649 --> 00:39:47,051
She's so fast.

926
00:39:47,118 --> 00:39:48,285
The master of school meals.

927
00:39:48,352 --> 00:39:49,920
She's so fast.

928
00:39:49,987 --> 00:39:51,489
The master of school meals with a knife.

929
00:39:51,555 --> 00:39:53,424
THE MESSI OF CHOPPING

930
00:39:53,491 --> 00:39:55,526
She just needs to make one serving,

931
00:39:55,593 --> 00:39:58,629
-but she's cooking for like ten.
-Exactly.

932
00:39:58,696 --> 00:39:59,663
Chef Mi-yeong.

933
00:39:59,730 --> 00:40:02,233
-You don't have to do that.
-That's her habit.

934
00:40:02,299 --> 00:40:04,301
THAT'S THE MASTER
OF SCHOOL MEALS

935
00:40:04,368 --> 00:40:06,537
-Shredded radish salad.
-Shredded radish salad.

936
00:40:06,604 --> 00:40:08,773
THE MASTER OF CHINESE CUISINE
SLAMS THE GARLIC CLOVE FLAT

937
00:40:09,340 --> 00:40:10,775
HE USES HIS GO-TO MOVE
TO GET ATTENTION

938
00:40:10,841 --> 00:40:12,777
Things get rowdy just as we speak.

939
00:40:12,843 --> 00:40:15,112
The two master chefs are chopping.

940
00:40:15,179 --> 00:40:17,148
"You can chop, I will slam."

941
00:40:17,915 --> 00:40:19,483
-"How dare you chop?"
-"You chop, I'll slam."

942
00:40:20,084 --> 00:40:22,253
THE TWO MASTERS ARE
ALREADY BATTLING FIERCELY

943
00:40:22,319 --> 00:40:24,388
-It's been three minutes already.
-Yes.

944
00:40:24,455 --> 00:40:26,891
-It's been that long?
-We're just past three minutes.

945
00:40:27,458 --> 00:40:30,127
BOK SHOW: 3. ADD CRAB
TO THE BROTH AND BRING TO A BOIL

946
00:40:30,194 --> 00:40:32,997
4. COOL COOKED OCTOPUS
IN COLD WATER

947
00:40:34,398 --> 00:40:37,034
He's chopping bulgogi finely,
so it must be dumpling filling.

948
00:40:37,101 --> 00:40:38,636
-Yes, it is.
-It's the filling?

949
00:40:38,702 --> 00:40:40,438
He's using that as the filling?

950
00:40:40,504 --> 00:40:42,506
It'll probably taste like galbi dumplings.

951
00:40:42,573 --> 00:40:44,542
-Right?
-Galbi dumplings.

952
00:40:45,443 --> 00:40:47,211
-That's sugar.
-Sugar?

953
00:40:47,278 --> 00:40:51,148
Yes, bulgogi is already seasoned,
but he added more sugar.

954
00:40:51,215 --> 00:40:53,384
-Youngtak, do you like sweet food?
-Well…

955
00:40:53,451 --> 00:40:54,552
I don't prefer sweet food.

956
00:40:56,520 --> 00:40:58,823
-That must've been too much sugar.
-Yes.

957
00:40:58,889 --> 00:41:01,292
-Oh, no.
-He can't revert that.

958
00:41:02,560 --> 00:41:05,095
-I'll do it over.
-Lee Yeon-bok looks flustered.

959
00:41:05,162 --> 00:41:06,997
-He's flustered.
-This is crazy.

960
00:41:07,565 --> 00:41:09,333
HE MAKES THE FILLING AGAIN

961
00:41:09,400 --> 00:41:11,902
THE OLD VERSION, THE NEW ONE

962
00:41:11,969 --> 00:41:14,472
CHOPPING THE BULGOGI,
THE 2ND TIME

963
00:41:15,072 --> 00:41:16,740
HE'LL COOK TO THE
FRIDGE OWNER'S APPETITE

964
00:41:16,807 --> 00:41:17,875
EVEN AS HE RUNS OUT OF TIME

965
00:41:18,676 --> 00:41:20,644
-It's on fire.
-There's fire.

966
00:41:20,711 --> 00:41:22,680
-He stir-fried it again.
-He made it over.

967
00:41:22,746 --> 00:41:24,782
-He spent some unexpected time.
-Yes.

968
00:41:24,849 --> 00:41:28,185
Youngtak's taste is the absolute measure.

969
00:41:28,252 --> 00:41:31,655
-Youngtak is important. He's the judge.
-That's right.

970
00:41:31,722 --> 00:41:33,090
-My gosh.
-Gosh.

971
00:41:33,157 --> 00:41:35,693
-They have ten minutes left.
-Yes.

972
00:41:35,759 --> 00:41:38,162
Already? We're at ten minutes already?

973
00:41:38,229 --> 00:41:40,130
COVERING HIS MOUTH IN SHOCK

974
00:41:41,098 --> 00:41:43,601
Chef Mi-yeong chops shishito peppers.

975
00:41:43,667 --> 00:41:47,104
She begins by seasoning the peppers.

976
00:41:47,171 --> 00:41:49,940
I've never seasoned these
with doenjang before,

977
00:41:50,007 --> 00:41:52,610
but they were all I could find,
so I wanted to try it.

978
00:41:52,676 --> 00:41:55,012
-Can you do it with regular pepper?
-Yes.

979
00:41:55,079 --> 00:41:58,249
Chef Mi-yeong makes the sauce
to season the shishito peppers with.

980
00:41:58,315 --> 00:41:59,149
4. MIX PEPPERS WITH DOENJANG,
STARCH SYRUP,

981
00:41:59,216 --> 00:42:00,050
MINCED GARLIC, SESAME OIL

982
00:42:00,117 --> 00:42:03,554
Chef Mi-yeong doesn't rush.
She cooks calmly and slowly.

983
00:42:03,621 --> 00:42:07,024
She cooks slowly and calmly,
yet she's also fast.

984
00:42:08,526 --> 00:42:10,761
SEASONED SHISHITO
PEPPERS, FINISHED

985
00:42:10,828 --> 00:42:13,564
She's making shredded radish salad
as the side dish.

986
00:42:13,631 --> 00:42:16,634
It takes a while to salt the radish.

987
00:42:16,700 --> 00:42:19,003
I think it'll turn out too raw.

988
00:42:19,069 --> 00:42:22,006
Many people make
shredded radish salad at home.

989
00:42:23,073 --> 00:42:24,241
Salt.

990
00:42:24,308 --> 00:42:28,345
Do you have a secret
to making delicious radish salad?

991
00:42:28,412 --> 00:42:29,547
I use plum syrup.

992
00:42:29,613 --> 00:42:31,348
-Plum syrup?
-Yes.

993
00:42:31,415 --> 00:42:34,184
SHE ADDS THE SECRET
INGREDIENT, PLUM SYRUP

994
00:42:34,251 --> 00:42:36,754
-Is that vinegar?
-Yes.

995
00:42:36,820 --> 00:42:38,589
MISS, WHOA!

996
00:42:38,656 --> 00:42:42,192
The vinegar shoots out
and makes a whole scene.

997
00:42:42,259 --> 00:42:44,094
Yes, she couldn't aim.

998
00:42:44,161 --> 00:42:47,097
Don't the chefs need earplugs?

999
00:42:47,164 --> 00:42:49,867
It'll shake our very identity.

1000
00:42:49,934 --> 00:42:51,702
That'll shake our very foundation.

1001
00:42:51,769 --> 00:42:54,638
It'll destroy the essence
of <i>Chef & My Fridge</i>.

1002
00:42:55,205 --> 00:42:58,509
SHE REGAINS HER CALM
AND FINISHES BY MIXING

1003
00:42:58,576 --> 00:43:00,911
-She already sets the radish salad.
-It's already done?

1004
00:43:00,978 --> 00:43:03,314
Chef Mi-yeong is a fast cook.

1005
00:43:03,380 --> 00:43:05,583
She already made
the pepper and radish side dishes.

1006
00:43:05,649 --> 00:43:07,284
While she's done making radish salad,

1007
00:43:07,351 --> 00:43:10,854
we don't even see a shadow
of Chef Yeon-bok's dumplings.

1008
00:43:10,921 --> 00:43:13,290
He's now fermenting the dough.

1009
00:43:13,357 --> 00:43:14,692
The dough is fermenting?

1010
00:43:14,758 --> 00:43:19,029
-Will it be dumpling skin and flour cake?
-Yes.

1011
00:43:19,630 --> 00:43:23,100
HE LEAVES THE DOUGH
AND MAKES THE TTEOKBOKKI SAUCE

1012
00:43:23,167 --> 00:43:28,038
-His mother's meal preps are useful.
-Yes, they're very useful.

1013
00:43:28,105 --> 00:43:29,139
It saves them time.

1014
00:43:29,707 --> 00:43:31,442
7. OIL PAN AND STIR-FRY ONION,
ZUCCHINI,

1015
00:43:31,508 --> 00:43:32,710
AND SPICY RED PEPPER POWDER

1016
00:43:33,243 --> 00:43:36,347
8. ADD SEAFOOD BROTH
TO THE MIXED VEGGIES

1017
00:43:36,914 --> 00:43:38,749
LEE YEON-BOK TASTES THE DISH

1018
00:43:39,316 --> 00:43:41,185
HE WANTS TO ADD MORE SEASONING

1019
00:43:41,251 --> 00:43:45,089
IS HE OILING HIS HANDS?

1020
00:43:45,723 --> 00:43:48,092
HE MISTOOK IT FOR SUGAR

1021
00:43:48,659 --> 00:43:50,094
THE RETURNING MASTER
GETS NERVOUS

1022
00:43:50,160 --> 00:43:51,862
COMPETING FOR THE FIRST TIME
IN 5 YEARS

1023
00:43:52,429 --> 00:43:54,832
HE QUICKLY CHANGES THE GLOVES

1024
00:43:55,933 --> 00:43:57,968
-He's making flour cake.
-He's making it!

1025
00:43:58,035 --> 00:43:59,370
HE'S FINALLY ON THE DOUGH

1026
00:44:03,607 --> 00:44:06,877
Chef Yeon-bok is making
flour cakes for <i>tteokbokki</i>.

1027
00:44:08,345 --> 00:44:10,814
Will that thick rice cake
get fully cooked in time?

1028
00:44:10,881 --> 00:44:13,751
But he did make the dough with hot water.

1029
00:44:13,817 --> 00:44:15,719
10. COOK FLOUR CAKE
IN BOILING WATER

1030
00:44:15,786 --> 00:44:17,354
The flour cake went into the water.

1031
00:44:17,421 --> 00:44:18,922
WILL THE FLOUR CAKE COOK
IN TIME?

1032
00:44:19,523 --> 00:44:21,291
Chief Yeon-bok makes dumpling skins.

1033
00:44:21,358 --> 00:44:24,294
We're starting to see
the dumplings come together.

1034
00:44:24,361 --> 00:44:25,896
He should make the skin.

1035
00:44:25,963 --> 00:44:28,799
Chef Eun-yeong is
good at making dumplings too.

1036
00:44:28,866 --> 00:44:32,336
Yes, but he's amazing.
He's making dumplings right now.

1037
00:44:33,370 --> 00:44:36,206
IN CONFUSION
BUT…

1038
00:44:36,273 --> 00:44:38,275
Wait, where's gochujang?

1039
00:44:38,342 --> 00:44:39,843
There it is.

1040
00:44:39,910 --> 00:44:41,111
Lee Yeon-bok is flustered!

1041
00:44:41,178 --> 00:44:44,982
-Wait, this is bad.
-Lee Yeon-bok is flustered!

1042
00:44:45,049 --> 00:44:47,217
12. MIX GOCHUJANG, TUNA SAUCE,
CHEONGYANG PEPPER TO BROTH

1043
00:44:47,284 --> 00:44:48,152
AND MAKE SAUCE

1044
00:44:48,218 --> 00:44:51,155
The thing is…
Master Yeon-bok is in trouble.

1045
00:44:51,221 --> 00:44:53,724
He may not finish the dish
for the opening match.

1046
00:44:54,591 --> 00:44:56,160
It's the opening match too. This is bad.

1047
00:44:56,226 --> 00:44:57,761
When will you use the crabs?

1048
00:44:58,429 --> 00:45:00,698
WILL HE COMPLETE HIS DISH
FOR THE OPENING MATCH?

1049
00:45:00,764 --> 00:45:03,267
HOW ABOUT THE OPENING MATCH DISH
FOR THE MASTER OF SCHOOL MEALS?

1050
00:45:03,333 --> 00:45:05,202
I'll add some cooking wine.

1051
00:45:06,737 --> 00:45:08,138
6. ADD COOKING WINE,
MINCED GARLIC,

1052
00:45:08,205 --> 00:45:09,807
SPICY RED PEPPER POWDER,
SUGAR, AND BOIL

1053
00:45:10,374 --> 00:45:17,281
7. ADD CHOPPED OCTOPUS AND
TUNA SAUCE, THEN BRING TO A BOIL

1054
00:45:17,347 --> 00:45:19,316
You have five minutes left.

1055
00:45:19,383 --> 00:45:22,219
-Sung-ju! Go and check them on the field.
-Yes?

1056
00:45:23,487 --> 00:45:24,354
THE EXHILARATING TIME

1057
00:45:24,421 --> 00:45:25,989
It's that time.

1058
00:45:26,557 --> 00:45:28,325
Please don't go.

1059
00:45:28,392 --> 00:45:30,661
LIPS GETTING DRY

1060
00:45:30,728 --> 00:45:32,129
-Should I go?
-You must!

1061
00:45:32,196 --> 00:45:33,831
All right! I'll go.

1062
00:45:33,897 --> 00:45:35,632
Let me run out to the field.

1063
00:45:35,699 --> 00:45:36,567
DASHING WITH ALL HIS MIGHT

1064
00:45:37,234 --> 00:45:38,836
It's time to taste the dishes.

1065
00:45:38,902 --> 00:45:41,538
That's right.
I'm Reporter Kim Sung-ju out on the field.

1066
00:45:41,605 --> 00:45:43,474
-Chef Mi-yeong.
-My gosh.

1067
00:45:43,540 --> 00:45:45,542
That's the toughest moment.

1068
00:45:45,609 --> 00:45:47,277
I hate it so much.

1069
00:45:47,344 --> 00:45:48,612
It's the worst.

1070
00:45:48,679 --> 00:45:51,749
She's adding green onion.

1071
00:45:51,815 --> 00:45:53,317
What's this for?

1072
00:45:53,383 --> 00:45:56,687
-It's for the braised kimchi.
-For this, braised octopus and kimchi.

1073
00:45:56,754 --> 00:45:57,755
Can you taste the soup?

1074
00:45:57,821 --> 00:46:00,124
Let me taste the soup
for the braised octopus and kimchi.

1075
00:46:00,190 --> 00:46:02,259
CHECKING THE SOUP
FOR BRAISED OCTOPUS AND KIMCHI

1076
00:46:02,326 --> 00:46:06,597
Does it taste good enough
to give energy to Tak?

1077
00:46:08,031 --> 00:46:12,336
It's too salty!

1078
00:46:13,470 --> 00:46:14,638
It's too salty!

1079
00:46:14,705 --> 00:46:16,006
GETTING UP

1080
00:46:16,073 --> 00:46:17,574
-It's too salty!
-No!

1081
00:46:17,641 --> 00:46:19,376
AN UNBELIEVABLE SAD NEWS

1082
00:46:19,443 --> 00:46:21,178
It'll get saltier when she boils it down!

1083
00:46:21,245 --> 00:46:23,680
It's too salty.

1084
00:46:23,747 --> 00:46:26,383
It's fine.

1085
00:46:26,450 --> 00:46:28,051
It's fine!

1086
00:46:28,118 --> 00:46:30,420
-Let me check one more time.
-Once more.

1087
00:46:30,487 --> 00:46:31,722
What was that?

1088
00:46:31,789 --> 00:46:33,924
I mean, this is…

1089
00:46:33,991 --> 00:46:35,793
So? How is it?

1090
00:46:35,859 --> 00:46:39,062
It's too salty!

1091
00:46:39,630 --> 00:46:40,864
THE MASTER'S DISH IS TOO SALTY?

1092
00:46:40,931 --> 00:46:43,500
-What now?
-Chef Mi-yeong pours sugar.

1093
00:46:43,567 --> 00:46:46,236
-She's pouring sugar in.
-She's pouring sugar in.

1094
00:46:46,303 --> 00:46:49,039
-What now?
-Chef Mi-yeong pours sugar.

1095
00:46:49,106 --> 00:46:52,075
-She's pouring sugar in.
-She's pouring sugar in.

1096
00:46:52,142 --> 00:46:55,045
-But she reflected my opinion.
-You said it was fine.

1097
00:46:55,112 --> 00:46:58,816
If the kimchi isn't cut,
I usually wash out the sauce.

1098
00:46:58,882 --> 00:47:01,985
You need to move quickly!

1099
00:47:02,052 --> 00:47:05,556
You must keep moving your hands
even as you speak.

1100
00:47:05,622 --> 00:47:08,058
Chef Yeon-bok also looks quite busy.

1101
00:47:08,125 --> 00:47:10,227
13. ADD STIR-FRIED BULGOGI
IN THE SKIN,

1102
00:47:10,294 --> 00:47:11,728
MAKE DUMPLING, AND DEEP-FRY

1103
00:47:11,795 --> 00:47:14,164
TREMBLING

1104
00:47:15,465 --> 00:47:17,835
He's throwing dumplings in.

1105
00:47:18,869 --> 00:47:20,904
Hey, what?

1106
00:47:20,971 --> 00:47:23,207
-Darn it.
-What's wrong, Lee Yeon-bok?

1107
00:47:23,273 --> 00:47:25,075
-I didn't light the stove.
-You didn't?

1108
00:47:25,142 --> 00:47:26,977
Goodness, Lee Yeon-bok.

1109
00:47:27,044 --> 00:47:29,546
Oh, my gosh. What will he do now?

1110
00:47:29,613 --> 00:47:30,981
Is this how it always is?

1111
00:47:31,048 --> 00:47:32,416
-Is it?
-Yes, it's always like this.

1112
00:47:32,482 --> 00:47:34,418
-What are you making?
-<i>Tteokbokki</i> sauce.

1113
00:47:34,484 --> 00:47:38,355
Let me taste the <i>tteokbokki</i> sauce
with 2 minutes and 24 seconds left.

1114
00:47:38,422 --> 00:47:40,490
Let me taste the <i>tteokbokki</i> sauce.

1115
00:47:40,557 --> 00:47:42,159
The <i>tteokbokki</i> sauce.

1116
00:47:42,226 --> 00:47:43,861
Can he do a tour of Bok Show?

1117
00:47:43,927 --> 00:47:48,465
It's a bit sweet!

1118
00:47:48,532 --> 00:47:49,399
BURST OUT LAUGHING

1119
00:47:49,967 --> 00:47:52,502
A SERIES OF SAD NEWS

1120
00:47:52,569 --> 00:47:55,038
-Bok Show!
-Isn't <i>tteokbokki</i> supposed to be sweet?

1121
00:47:55,739 --> 00:47:58,008
Well, this is my personal take.

1122
00:47:58,075 --> 00:48:00,577
I like it because I like sweet food.

1123
00:48:00,644 --> 00:48:02,412
-I thought it was a bit sweet.
-It can be.

1124
00:48:02,479 --> 00:48:04,948
But Youngtak said
he doesn't prefer sweet food.

1125
00:48:05,015 --> 00:48:06,049
You're right.

1126
00:48:06,617 --> 00:48:09,253
GETTING THE FLOUR CAKE
IN THE MIDST OF CHAOS

1127
00:48:09,319 --> 00:48:11,989
14. PUT COOKED FLOUR CAKE
INTO THE SAUCE AND BOIL

1128
00:48:12,556 --> 00:48:17,194
15. ADD CHOPPED OCTOPUS
INTO TTEOKBOKKI AND BOIL

1129
00:48:17,261 --> 00:48:19,429
8. ADD SLICED GREEN ONION
AND RED PEPPER

1130
00:48:19,496 --> 00:48:21,164
INTO BRAISED OCTOPUS AND KIMCHI

1131
00:48:21,932 --> 00:48:23,600
THE MASTER OF SCHOOL MEALS
SERVES

1132
00:48:23,667 --> 00:48:25,269
THE BRAISED OCTOPUS AND KIMCHI

1133
00:48:25,335 --> 00:48:26,637
-Yes.
-She's ready.

1134
00:48:26,703 --> 00:48:28,538
-Is Chef Mi-yeong done?
-Is she?

1135
00:48:28,605 --> 00:48:31,942
-She's already serving.
-She still has 1 minute and 53 seconds.

1136
00:48:32,009 --> 00:48:35,012
-He's still making dumplings.
-We have 1 minute and 53 seconds.

1137
00:48:35,078 --> 00:48:36,914
-Already?
-Are you all right?

1138
00:48:36,980 --> 00:48:38,882
She's already done with it.

1139
00:48:38,949 --> 00:48:41,685
-I think she's serving it.
-Already?

1140
00:48:41,752 --> 00:48:43,887
Chef Mi-yeong is almost done.
She's about to ring the bell.

1141
00:48:43,954 --> 00:48:46,089
Let's go.

1142
00:48:46,156 --> 00:48:47,925
-The rice.
-What about the rice?

1143
00:48:47,991 --> 00:48:50,093
-The rice.
-What about the rice?

1144
00:48:50,160 --> 00:48:53,397
-The rice!
-Wait, she rings the bell!

1145
00:48:53,463 --> 00:48:56,033
-We have 1 minute and 30 seconds.
-You didn't get the rice!

1146
00:48:56,099 --> 00:48:58,568
-A minute and 30 seconds.
-Rice! The rice!

1147
00:48:58,635 --> 00:49:01,004
RIGHT, THE RICE…

1148
00:49:02,773 --> 00:49:05,275
-There's no rice!
-There's no rice!

1149
00:49:05,342 --> 00:49:07,911
SHE HAS 1 MINUTE
AND 27 SECONDS LEFT

1150
00:49:07,978 --> 00:49:10,881
-There was no rice.
-How can this be?

1151
00:49:11,481 --> 00:49:14,451
She would've been eliminated
on <i>Culinary Class Wars</i>.

1152
00:49:14,518 --> 00:49:17,321
THEY BOTH GET ANXIOUS TOO

1153
00:49:17,387 --> 00:49:19,456
I can't open this.

1154
00:49:20,090 --> 00:49:23,160
-She'll serve cold rice.
-She didn't serve rice.

1155
00:49:23,226 --> 00:49:24,995
EDWARD HELPS RIGHT AWAY

1156
00:49:25,762 --> 00:49:26,797
UNI-CHEF FROM AMERICA

1157
00:49:26,863 --> 00:49:29,766
Will Edward do it for her?

1158
00:49:29,833 --> 00:49:30,968
Kyun just helped her.

1159
00:49:31,034 --> 00:49:34,237
-It would've been bad if we didn't say it.
-It would've been so bad!

1160
00:49:34,304 --> 00:49:37,107
-She didn't serve rice!
-It would've been bad.

1161
00:49:37,174 --> 00:49:39,443
-She didn't have rice.
-How can he eat it without rice?

1162
00:49:39,509 --> 00:49:41,511
I smell something burning.

1163
00:49:41,578 --> 00:49:43,413
-Their insides are burning.
-What's burning?

1164
00:49:43,480 --> 00:49:45,749
-Their insides?
-Yes, their insides.

1165
00:49:45,816 --> 00:49:47,351
Their insides are completely burnt.

1166
00:49:47,417 --> 00:49:48,385
Chef Mi-yeong, we need the rice.

1167
00:49:48,452 --> 00:49:49,987
Her insides are burning because of rice.

1168
00:49:50,053 --> 00:49:51,121
SHE LOSES HER COMPOSURE

1169
00:49:51,188 --> 00:49:52,789
-And it's ready.
-Look!

1170
00:49:52,856 --> 00:49:55,058
-Chef Yeon-bok.
-They have one minute.

1171
00:49:55,125 --> 00:49:58,362
He cooked three dumplings.

1172
00:49:58,428 --> 00:50:03,300
We're now under 1 minute.
We have 50 seconds left.

1173
00:50:03,367 --> 00:50:04,501
GULPING

1174
00:50:04,568 --> 00:50:06,670
Gosh, right now…

1175
00:50:06,737 --> 00:50:09,373
-He's getting crab meat ready.
-Thirty seconds!

1176
00:50:09,439 --> 00:50:12,876
Yes, he has 30 seconds.
Chef Yeon-bok is at a disadvantage.

1177
00:50:12,943 --> 00:50:14,945
What will he do with the crab?

1178
00:50:15,012 --> 00:50:17,314
He's serving the <i>tteokbokki</i>.

1179
00:50:17,381 --> 00:50:19,449
-It needs to look nice too.
-Yes.

1180
00:50:19,516 --> 00:50:20,951
You have 19, no, 20 seconds left.

1181
00:50:21,018 --> 00:50:23,186
Youngtak said he likes well-plated dishes.

1182
00:50:23,253 --> 00:50:24,855
You have 19, no, 20 seconds left.

1183
00:50:24,921 --> 00:50:27,324
ON THE OTHER HAND, THE MASTER
OF SCHOOL MEALS IS ANXIOUS

1184
00:50:27,391 --> 00:50:28,925
Yes, the crab meat.

1185
00:50:28,992 --> 00:50:31,995
You have ten seconds. Let's countdown.

1186
00:50:32,062 --> 00:50:33,997
-Ten. Nine.
-Nine.

1187
00:50:34,064 --> 00:50:35,932
-Eight. Seven.
-Eight. Seven.

1188
00:50:35,999 --> 00:50:38,435
-I'm done.
-Six. Five.

