Choi Hyun-suk is such a great chef,

1421
01:01:22,078 --> 01:01:24,881
-so I'll use the one-minute stop.
-The stop!

1422
01:01:24,947 --> 01:01:26,382
The one-minute stop.

1423
01:01:26,949 --> 01:01:29,318
-He'll stop him because he's good.
-Because he's good.

1424
01:01:29,385 --> 01:01:30,920
-He's good.
-He's good.

1425
01:01:30,987 --> 01:01:35,391
What do I do if I want to make him stop?
Do I just shout it out?

1426
01:01:35,458 --> 01:01:38,628
-You can just shout out, "Stop!"
-This is just…

1427
01:01:38,695 --> 01:01:40,963
-May I ask Youngtak something?
-Sure.

1428
01:01:41,030 --> 01:01:42,799
Are you okay with undercooked food?

1429
01:01:42,865 --> 01:01:45,768
Yes, I like undercooked food.

1430
01:01:45,835 --> 01:01:47,470
THANK YOU

1431
01:01:47,537 --> 01:01:48,738
He likes undercooked food.

1432
01:01:48,805 --> 01:01:51,541
What he likes is a fun show.

1433
01:01:51,607 --> 01:01:55,445
Do you have all the ingredients you need?

1434
01:01:55,511 --> 01:01:56,779
I need oyster.

1435
01:01:56,846 --> 01:01:58,448
Oyster. Do you want me to share?

1436
01:01:58,514 --> 01:02:00,283
-Please.
-Sharing the oyster? He should.

1437
01:02:00,349 --> 01:02:01,984
There was only one pack.

1438
01:02:02,051 --> 01:02:03,920
Is Chef Hyun-suk hoarding the oyster?

1439
01:02:03,986 --> 01:02:04,887
How many?

1440
01:02:07,156 --> 01:02:08,725
TAKING OUT

1441
01:02:08,791 --> 01:02:12,361
-What?
-What?

1442
01:02:12,428 --> 01:02:13,896
I'll give you this.

1443
01:02:14,731 --> 01:02:16,666
YOU AREN'T SO BAD

1444
01:02:16,733 --> 01:02:19,869
My gosh, the tension is high.

1445
01:02:19,936 --> 01:02:21,904
-He's giving him a few.
-I thought he'd take the bowl.

1446
01:02:26,542 --> 01:02:28,678
INGREDIENTS OVER CHEFS,
FRIENDS OVER INGREDIENTS

1447
01:02:28,745 --> 01:02:30,379
-The production crew gave me an intel.
-Yes?

1448
01:02:30,446 --> 01:02:35,618
Chef Edward apparently took
one of the facial masks from the fridge.

1449
01:02:35,685 --> 01:02:36,953
What? Why?

1450
01:02:37,520 --> 01:02:38,421
JUST NOW

1451
01:02:41,524 --> 01:02:42,892
WHY DOES HE NEED THE FACE MASK?

1452
01:02:42,959 --> 01:02:45,361
-That's not food.
-Why? Do you need it to cook?

1453
01:02:45,428 --> 01:02:47,997
I was curious about it.

1454
01:02:48,064 --> 01:02:49,766
-He was curious.
-He was just curious.

1455
01:02:49,832 --> 01:02:51,334
I've never done it before.

1456
01:02:51,400 --> 01:02:54,804
He's never done it before,
so he took the facial masks.

1457
01:02:54,871 --> 01:02:56,739
It's not for the food.

1458
01:02:56,806 --> 01:02:57,840
-Sung-ju.
-Yes?

1459
01:02:57,907 --> 01:03:00,209
You three are friends, right?
Who are you rooting for?

1460
01:03:00,276 --> 01:03:01,711
-Me?
-Yes.

1461
01:03:01,778 --> 01:03:03,913
LAUGHING OUT LOUD

1462
01:03:03,980 --> 01:03:05,148
You're putting me in a spot.

1463
01:03:05,214 --> 01:03:06,983
-I'm good friends with Hyun-suk.
-Yes.

1464
01:03:07,049 --> 01:03:08,985
-And I like Kyun too.
-Sure.

1465
01:03:09,051 --> 01:03:12,321
Gosh, this is a toughie.

1466
01:03:12,388 --> 01:03:13,723
I'm on Team Kyun today.

1467
01:03:13,790 --> 01:03:16,425
SHOWING HIS CHARMS

1468
01:03:16,492 --> 01:03:19,862
I'm on Team Kyun. He had to travel far.

1469
01:03:19,929 --> 01:03:21,597
-He came on a plane.
-Yes.

1470
01:03:21,664 --> 01:03:25,902
He flies in for 15 hours
only to fight for 15 minutes.

1471
01:03:25,968 --> 01:03:28,304
-You're right.
-That's right.

1472
01:03:28,371 --> 01:03:30,273
Fifteen hours.

1473
01:03:30,673 --> 01:03:32,942
CHEF CHOI HYUN-SUK'S INGREDIENTS

1474
01:03:33,009 --> 01:03:34,243
EGGS, OYSTER, CRAB, BUTTER,
BROTH PACK, MILK,

1475
01:03:34,310 --> 01:03:35,178
TUNA SAUCE, SALTED SHRIMP

1476
01:03:35,244 --> 01:03:38,080
Chef Hyun-suk, what will you cook today?

1477
01:03:38,147 --> 01:03:41,017
I'm going to make an omelet for him.

1478
01:03:41,083 --> 01:03:42,018
-Omelet?
-Omelet?

1479
01:03:42,084 --> 01:03:46,722
Omelet is the most basic
and the most classic egg dish.

1480
01:03:46,789 --> 01:03:49,292
-Yes.
-I'll turn this basic omelet

1481
01:03:49,358 --> 01:03:52,261
into something special and luxurious,

1482
01:03:52,328 --> 01:03:54,463
a wonderful dish.

1483
01:03:54,530 --> 01:03:55,665
-Today,
-Gosh.

1484
01:03:55,731 --> 01:03:56,966
-my dish is called…
-It's called?

1485
01:03:57,033 --> 01:03:58,601
THIS IS MY FAVORITE PART

1486
01:03:58,668 --> 01:04:01,871
-The Egg Is on Fire.
-The egg.

1487
01:04:01,938 --> 01:04:03,306
-The Egg Is…
-On Fire.

1488
01:04:03,372 --> 01:04:06,409
<i>Jingle, jingle, jingle, jingle</i>

1489
01:04:06,475 --> 01:04:09,645
WILL THIS RETURNING CHEF
COOK LIKE HE'S ON FIRE?

1490
01:04:09,712 --> 01:04:10,546
CHEF EDWARD LEE'S INGREDIENTS

1491
01:04:10,613 --> 01:04:11,581
EGGS, OYSTER,
BALSAMIC VINEGAR, JALAPENO

1492
01:04:11,647 --> 01:04:12,481
ENOKI MUSHROOM, MAYONNAISE,
SOY SAUCE,

1493
01:04:12,548 --> 01:04:13,382
CHOGOCHUJANG, SESAME OIL,
FACE MASK(?)

1494
01:04:13,783 --> 01:04:15,952
My dish is…

1495
01:04:16,018 --> 01:04:17,153
Yes, what's it called?

1496
01:04:17,787 --> 01:04:19,622
It's not Edward,

1497
01:04:19,689 --> 01:04:22,425
-but Eggward.
-Eggward.

1498
01:04:22,491 --> 01:04:25,862
-Eggward Lee.
-Eggward Lee.

1499
01:04:25,928 --> 01:04:28,798
-His dish is called Eggward.
-Eggward Lee.

1500
01:04:28,865 --> 01:04:29,799
That's crazy.

1501
01:04:29,866 --> 01:04:33,436
When I was younger,
my family didn't have enough money,

1502
01:04:33,502 --> 01:04:35,471
so we ate simple meals.

1503
01:04:35,538 --> 01:04:40,076
So we always had rice, raw egg,

1504
01:04:40,142 --> 01:04:42,678
-and soy sauce.
-I see.

1505
01:04:42,745 --> 01:04:43,880
-Gosh.
-He's right.

1506
01:04:43,946 --> 01:04:45,281
We all ate that a lot.

1507
01:04:45,348 --> 01:04:46,949
Though it may be simple,

1508
01:04:47,016 --> 01:04:51,187
I still remember enjoying it so much.

1509
01:04:51,254 --> 01:04:52,188
IT WAS STILL A DELICIOUS MEMORY

1510
01:04:52,255 --> 01:04:55,391
I wanted to remember that taste today

1511
01:04:55,458 --> 01:04:58,661
and elevate it a little

1512
01:04:58,728 --> 01:05:01,530
-to make an unusual version of that.
-That's great.

1513
01:05:01,597 --> 01:05:03,599
What concerns you the most?

1514
01:05:03,666 --> 01:05:06,702
I'm going to make rice first.

1515
01:05:06,769 --> 01:05:09,839
-He'll make rice first.
-He'll do that first.

1516
01:05:09,906 --> 01:05:11,974
-That's smart.
-I picked it up quickly.

1517
01:05:13,376 --> 01:05:15,578
He learned it from Chef Mi-yeong.

1518
01:05:15,645 --> 01:05:16,679
That's right.

1519
01:05:16,746 --> 01:05:19,782
Chef Edward has the perk
to stop the opponent for one minute.

1520
01:05:19,849 --> 01:05:24,353
Let us begin the egg paradise round.

1521
01:05:27,857 --> 01:05:29,158
Gosh.

1522
01:05:29,225 --> 01:05:30,993
THE TWO WHITE SPOON CHEFS ARE
FINALLY IN A COOK-OFF

1523
01:05:31,060 --> 01:05:33,129
A top contributor for <i>Chef & My Fridge</i>

1524
01:05:33,195 --> 01:05:35,064
and the strongest presence
of <i>Culinary Class Wars</i>.

1525
01:05:35,131 --> 01:05:36,699
Chef Choi Hyun-suk is

1526
01:05:36,766 --> 01:05:40,736
up against the winner of <i>Iron Chef </i>and
the chef of the White House state dinner,

1527
01:05:40,803 --> 01:05:44,974
the second place of <i>Culinary Class Wars</i>,
Chef Edward Lee.

1528
01:05:45,041 --> 01:05:49,979
Let us begin the 15-minute cook-off!

1529
01:05:50,046 --> 01:05:51,113
THE 15-MINUTE COOK-OFF BEGINS!

1530
01:05:51,180 --> 01:05:54,951
Let us begin!

1531
01:05:55,017 --> 01:05:57,453
IT'S A RIVAL ROUND!

1532
01:05:57,520 --> 01:06:00,256
I can't believe we get to see this match.

1533
01:06:00,323 --> 01:06:01,924
It's a fiery cooking match.

1534
01:06:01,991 --> 01:06:05,161
Edward Lee cracks the eggs first.

1535
01:06:05,227 --> 01:06:06,996
He cracks the eggs first.

1536
01:06:07,063 --> 01:06:09,265
NEXT, JUST AS HE LEARNED,
THE RICE FIRST

1537
01:06:09,999 --> 01:06:12,468
-He's making the rice.
-Right.

1538
01:06:12,535 --> 01:06:14,236
-He's timing the microwave.
-Yes.

1539
01:06:14,303 --> 01:06:18,007
He saw Chef Mi-yeong's mistake
and decided to make rice first.

1540
01:06:18,074 --> 01:06:19,475
That was a great choice.

1541
01:06:19,542 --> 01:06:20,776
BALSAMIC VINEGAR

1542
01:06:20,843 --> 01:06:24,814
Is he mixing soy sauce
and balsamic vinegar?

1543
01:06:24,880 --> 01:06:26,816
What? He's mixing soy sauce
and balsamic vinegar?

1544
01:06:26,882 --> 01:06:27,850
Gosh.

1545
01:06:27,917 --> 01:06:29,085
The vinegar won't come out.

1546
01:06:29,151 --> 01:06:30,686
What?

1547
01:06:30,753 --> 01:06:33,389
-It's new.
-It's not open yet.

1548
01:06:34,523 --> 01:06:35,858
STAY CALM

1549
01:06:36,425 --> 01:06:37,393
RESOLVED

1550
01:06:37,460 --> 01:06:39,695
It wasn't used, so it was stuck.

1551
01:06:39,762 --> 01:06:41,697
It was because he didn't use it.

1552
01:06:41,764 --> 01:06:44,667
Will soy sauce go well
with balsamic vinegar?

1553
01:06:44,734 --> 01:06:46,168
-Right?
-Do they?

1554
01:06:46,235 --> 01:06:48,838
A TASTE, AND A CAUTIOUS MOVE

1555
01:06:48,904 --> 01:06:49,839
A THUMB UP

1556
01:06:50,406 --> 01:06:52,441
Chef Hyun-suk is working with crab meat.

1557
01:06:52,508 --> 01:06:54,910
-He must be using crab meat.
-Yes.

1558
01:06:54,977 --> 01:06:58,314
He's getting the meat out,
then using the shell to make broth.

1559
01:06:58,381 --> 01:06:59,582
-I see.
-Yes.

1560
01:06:59,648 --> 01:07:01,317
2. BOIL BROTH PACK AND
CRAB SHELL TO MAKE BROTH

1561
01:07:02,218 --> 01:07:05,154
He's leaving out egg yolks
and only using the whites.

1562
01:07:05,221 --> 01:07:06,856
HE SEPARATES EGG WHITES, SUGAR

1563
01:07:06,922 --> 01:07:08,724
Edward Lee only uses the yolks.

1564
01:07:08,791 --> 01:07:11,327
He's only using the yolks.

1565
01:07:11,394 --> 01:07:13,229
He's getting the egg yolks.

1566
01:07:13,295 --> 01:07:14,663
He saves just the yolks.

1567
01:07:14,730 --> 01:07:16,132
-He's very careful.
-He's careful.

1568
01:07:16,198 --> 01:07:20,102
-I guess he can't break the yolk.
-He must need whole yolks.

1569
01:07:20,169 --> 01:07:22,304
-Marinated egg yolks.
-He's marinating them?

1570
01:07:22,371 --> 01:07:23,439
Isn't that so?

1571
01:07:24,106 --> 01:07:25,641
I guess he can't break it.

1572
01:07:25,708 --> 01:07:27,376
EVERYONE… LOOK HERE!

1573
01:07:27,443 --> 01:07:29,478
Choi Hyun-suk makes meringue!

1574
01:07:29,545 --> 01:07:31,580
SUDDENLY INTERESTED
THE CHEAT CODE, MAKING MERINGUE!

1575
01:07:31,647 --> 01:07:33,249
Look at his facial expression.

1576
01:07:33,315 --> 01:07:35,184
Choi Hyun-suk,
the meringue-whipping expert.

1577
01:07:35,251 --> 01:07:38,954
3. ADD SUGAR TO EGG WHITES
AND WHIP IT

1578
01:07:39,688 --> 01:07:42,191
ATTENTION IS MY POWER!

1579
01:07:42,258 --> 01:07:44,693
BUT MY ENERGY IS…

1580
01:07:44,760 --> 01:07:46,629
Do you need my help?

1581
01:07:46,695 --> 01:07:48,431
-I need your help.
-I'd love to help.

1582
01:07:48,497 --> 01:07:50,433
-Come and do it.
-I want to help.

1583
01:07:50,499 --> 01:07:52,535
-I want to help you.
-Look at Chef Hyun-suk.

1584
01:07:52,601 --> 01:07:55,438
-Choi Hyun-suk is getting old too.
-He is.

1585
01:07:55,504 --> 01:07:57,540
-He's over 50 now.
-He is.

1586
01:07:57,606 --> 01:07:59,909
He has frozen shoulders now.

1587
01:07:59,975 --> 01:08:01,310
HYUN-SUK NOW HAS
FROZEN SHOULDERS…

1588
01:08:02,244 --> 01:08:04,613
That's why he doesn't sprinkle salt.

1589
01:08:04,680 --> 01:08:05,881
WAS THAT THE REASON?

1590
01:08:05,948 --> 01:08:09,151
Choi Hyun-suk makes meringue
with a lot of effort.

1591
01:08:12,021 --> 01:08:14,056
It'll be funny if he stops him now.

1592
01:08:14,123 --> 01:08:16,392
If he stops him now,
it'll be a huge problem.

1593
01:08:16,459 --> 01:08:20,262
If he stops him here, that'll be the end.

1594
01:08:20,329 --> 01:08:21,764
Stop it.

1595
01:08:21,831 --> 01:08:22,665
STOPPING HERE RUINS THE MERINGUE

1596
01:08:22,731 --> 01:08:25,234
-He didn't see him.
-Balsamic vinegar and soy sauce.

1597
01:08:25,301 --> 01:08:29,338
Will the sauce seep into the yolk
if you leave it in there?

1598
01:08:29,405 --> 01:08:30,706
-It does.
-It does?

1599
01:08:30,773 --> 01:08:32,942
But will it happen in time?

1600
01:08:33,509 --> 01:08:36,445
CHOI HYUN-SUK'S EGG WHITES
TURNED INTO FOAM

1601
01:08:36,512 --> 01:08:37,413
Okay.

1602
01:08:37,913 --> 01:08:39,682
BEATS THE YOLKS

1603
01:08:39,748 --> 01:08:42,451
IF IT ISN'T RUNNY, IT'S DONE

1604
01:08:42,518 --> 01:08:43,586
PLEASED

1605
01:08:45,221 --> 01:08:46,589
He finished the meringue.

1606
01:08:46,655 --> 01:08:49,325
And he adds egg yolks too.

1607
01:08:49,391 --> 01:08:51,494
4. MIX SALTED YOLKS WITH THE
MERINGUE TO MAKE OMELET BATTER

1608
01:08:51,560 --> 01:08:56,198
There's the rice.
Edward has brought out the rice.

1609
01:08:56,265 --> 01:08:58,167
-The rice…
-He covers the rice.

1610
01:08:58,234 --> 01:08:59,568
He's rolling it.

1611
01:09:01,070 --> 01:09:03,672
-He's rolling it.
-So it's rice and eggs.

1612
01:09:03,739 --> 01:09:05,875
-He's rolling the rice out.
-Yes.

1613
01:09:05,941 --> 01:09:07,276
That's new.

1614
01:09:07,343 --> 01:09:09,778
He's putting seaweed on top.

1615
01:09:09,845 --> 01:09:11,514
Will he turn it into a rice ball?

1616
01:09:11,580 --> 01:09:13,282
Will he put it in the middle?

1617
01:09:13,349 --> 01:09:14,617
-He's now…
-It's rolled out.

1618
01:09:14,683 --> 01:09:15,651
A CIRCULAR CUTTER

1619
01:09:15,718 --> 01:09:16,852
A circular shape.

1620
01:09:16,919 --> 01:09:19,121
-He's shaping it.
-He's making a shape.

1621
01:09:19,188 --> 01:09:20,856
He's going to shape it too?

1622
01:09:20,923 --> 01:09:21,957
SHAKING

1623
01:09:22,024 --> 01:09:23,692
That's hard to do.

1624
01:09:25,494 --> 01:09:26,862
THE RICE SHAPE IS…

1625
01:09:26,929 --> 01:09:29,031
Did it work as he wanted?

1626
01:09:29,098 --> 01:09:31,534
-It's like a sandwich.
-I see.

1627
01:09:31,600 --> 01:09:33,569
The seaweed went in between the rice.

1628
01:09:34,136 --> 01:09:36,772
But Chef Edward forgot to use his perk.

1629
01:09:36,839 --> 01:09:38,274
I think he forgot his perk.

1630
01:09:38,340 --> 01:09:41,977
Chef Edward, I want to let you know
that you can stop for one minute.

1631
01:09:42,044 --> 01:09:44,547
You have ten minutes left.

1632
01:09:45,648 --> 01:09:47,983
-Oh, shoot.
-He says, "Oh, shoot."

1633
01:09:48,050 --> 01:09:49,418
CHECKING FOR TIME

1634
01:09:49,485 --> 01:09:52,555
Already? The time is flying.

1635
01:09:52,621 --> 01:09:54,757
It feels even faster when you cook.

1636
01:09:55,357 --> 01:09:56,192
CRAB MEAT

1637
01:09:56,258 --> 01:09:57,693
AND OYSTER

1638
01:09:57,760 --> 01:10:00,996
He's cooking oysters and crab together.

1639
01:10:01,063 --> 01:10:03,365
I'm cooking them together.

1640
01:10:03,432 --> 01:10:08,871
5. OIL PAN AND STIR-FRY
CRAB MEAT AND OYSTERS

1641
01:10:08,938 --> 01:10:10,206
NEXT, THE MAIN EVENT

1642
01:10:11,040 --> 01:10:13,576
The omelet batter goes in.

1643
01:10:13,642 --> 01:10:16,579
Omelet gets really soft when it's whipped.

1644
01:10:16,645 --> 01:10:17,780
A souffle omelet.

1645
01:10:17,846 --> 01:10:19,248
SOFT SOUFFLE OMELET

1646
01:10:20,382 --> 01:10:21,784
WHAT'S THE KICK FOR HIS OMELET?

1647
01:10:21,850 --> 01:10:24,420
He's putting those on the top.

1648
01:10:24,486 --> 01:10:25,521
Gosh.

1649
01:10:25,588 --> 01:10:27,389
He put the cooked crab meat on top.

1650
01:10:27,456 --> 01:10:29,024
It'll be really soft.

1651
01:10:29,091 --> 01:10:32,194
He topped the omelet with crab meat.

1652
01:10:32,261 --> 01:10:34,463
That has to be delicious.

1653
01:10:34,530 --> 01:10:35,898
That looks good.

1654
01:10:35,965 --> 01:10:38,133
CHECKING THE TEMPERATURE!

1655
01:10:38,200 --> 01:10:39,068
Will he fry those?

1656
01:10:39,134 --> 01:10:41,370
He's getting the oyster out. And flour.

1657
01:10:41,437 --> 01:10:43,639
He salts it too.

1658
01:10:43,706 --> 01:10:45,241
My gosh.

1659
01:10:45,307 --> 01:10:47,810
I have no idea what he's doing.

1660
01:10:47,876 --> 01:10:49,044
Will he fry those?

1661
01:10:53,582 --> 01:10:55,584
1-MINUTE STOP

